commit_message:
Remove strict requirements bounds

Existing requirements versions aren't compatible with
packages available in CentOS7, and must be updated.

In order to get it working we simply remove all upper bounds.
This is temporarily solutions, should be replaced by correct
version bounds.

Is NOT compatible with CentOS6 master node

commit_message:
Make check_md5 function generic

The check_md5 function is generic and belongs into functions-host.sh,
even though it is currently only used in virtualbox-install_base.sh.

This patch also touches up the status and error messages to make them
generic. The function now aborts if the file it is supposed to check
does not exist. In addition, it no longer removes a file if the MD5 sum
does not match, which gives the user a chance to investigate what
happened.

Change-Id: If0f3d8fd69645638ecc659d0d676a425cd8b3167

commit_message:
Handle faultstring when using SessionClient

When the magnum-api returns an error code 400-600, SessionClient
faultstring did not return to users. It should return a detailed
error message.

This commit was ported from Ironic:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/142021/

Change-Id: I8bc15c0ddab10f0e117fb6acb2f3995929fa65e2
Closes-Bug: #1520363

commit_message:
Validate external network when create a bay

For good user experience, we should validate if Baymodel's network
is existed in Bay creation. When create a Bay, a 404 NotFound will
be raised if external_network in Bay's Baymodel isn't existed.

Change-Id: Iec2e06380ca53268b85bcdd7d1539f5d10a09181
Patially-Implements: blueprint api-parameter-validation

commit_message:
[networking] Fix description of IPv6 RA flag for SLAAC

* Moves "Managed" to the next line. "Managed Configuration Flag"
  is one of the valid RA flags.
* Move "New or existing" to the beginning of the next paragraph.
  The meaning of the next sentence is still correct even after moving
  this. It is still true as IPv6 attributes of neutron subnet can
  be updated.

Change-Id: Ia764adc26f323d4909350beb875e082e07d0ea56

commit_message:
Support for new oslo namespaces

Updated oslo components uses oslo_* namespaces instead of oslo.*

It is required to support new ones because CentOS7 master node
also contains updated OpenStack components.

This commit adds support for those.

Blueprint: master-on-centos7

Compatible with CentOS6 master node

Change-Id: I798b5c3cf9b1f4777d93c399a7d245ab866dba0e

[config-ref] Convert some image-service files

not a distro specific one that might get outdated.

According to the word choice convention in
"http://docs.openstack.org/contributor-guide/writing-style/

We should use OpenStack instead of Openstack.

commit_message:
Adjust default nova_force_config_drive to be False

The default for nova_force_config_drive upstream is "false" there is a
TODO to adjust this in Liberty.

This patch completes that TODO and sets the var (removing the TODO
comment).

Change-Id: I2159464c852b72685ee1a81d169ab64b6a1cc4b9
Closes-Bug: #1520628

commit_message:
Adds test for mac_spoofing at network level

Test that MAC spoofing is enforced by Neutron security-groups and allowed
when port-security flag is turned off at network level.

Partially Implements: blueprint ml2-ovs-portsecurity

Change-Id: I54d7eeb46fde36c13c7afa240122d0809e1b1975

[{'created': '2015-11-27 19:39:17.000000000', 'message': 'Allow Horizon Custom Branding

This introduces 2 variables:
``horizon_site_name`` and ``horizon_custom_uploads``.

The former needs to set with a string. It will edit the
local settings of horizon to add the cloud's name.

The latter is a dict, that contains path to source and destination
files that the deployer wants to upload.
For example, if setting the dict as followed:

horizon_custom_uploads:
  logo:
    src: '/etc/openstack_deploy/files/logo.png'
    dest: "img/logo.png"
  logosplash:
    src: '/etc/openstack_deploy/files/logo-splash.png'
    dest: "img/logo-splash.png"

You'll overwrite the img/logo.png and img/logo-splash.png files
on the horizon nodes (inside their folder
"{{ horizon_lib_dir }}/openstack_dashboard/static/dashboard/")
with the files stored on the deployment node at the src location.

(cherry picked from commit 5c9594d4db8246759c917bef918e53fc26a87e80)
'}]
commit_message:
Allow Horizon Custom Branding

This introduces 2 variables:
``horizon_site_name`` and ``horizon_custom_uploads``.

The former needs to set with a string. It will edit the
local settings of horizon to add the cloud's name.

The latter is a dict, that contains path to source and destination
files that the deployer wants to upload.
For example, if setting the dict as followed:

horizon_custom_uploads:
  logo:
    src: '/etc/openstack_deploy/files/logo.png'
    dest: "img/logo.png"
  logosplash:
    src: '/etc/openstack_deploy/files/logo-splash.png'
    dest: "img/logo-splash.png"

You'll overwrite the img/logo.png and img/logo-splash.png files
on the horizon nodes (inside their folder
"{{ horizon_lib_dir }}/openstack_dashboard/static/dashboard/")
with the files stored on the deployment node at the src location.

Change-Id: I1a74e74968d09f6e299dbd965f9c87368c4d646c
(cherry picked from commit 5c9594d4db8246759c917bef918e53fc26a87e80)

commit_message:
Add support for glance task import

https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Glance-tasks-import
Added API for task create, delete and list
Added task image exception
Added wait_for_image for v2
Added wait_for_image_task v2
Added a testcase.
testcase description:
- creating a task for imported dummy image via http
- converting the disk_format for the image
- wait till new created image will be in ready status
- verify image disk_format and task status and type

I am planning to commit more tests for different disk formats.

Depends-On: I5fc1d768c5596c93871c73c4cabfa501ac484eb6
Change-Id: I18444c65d6acd66059c4537718376514e30fae9e

Update guides in README.rst

The networking guide does not present in the manuals
list in the README.rst. Also, the list contained two
obsolete guides.

Update the list.

commit_message:
Skip some functional tests for convergence until fixed

Skip the following functional tests for convergence gate:
  StackValidationTest
  UpdateStackTest.test_stack_update_alias_type
  and UpdateStackTest.test_stack_update_alias_changes

so that we can make the convergence gate mandatory to run.
Except this tests all should be passing in convergence.

Co-Authored-By: Rakesh H S <rh-s@hpe.com>

Change-Id: Ia973b3033b031eff7b3713c347630bf5d91d0377

Change namespace for Heat resources and tests

Change namespace to more specified.
Use path to specify resource or test should be enough.

commit_message:
Install yum-plugin-priorities on RHEL-derivatives

RDO provides all of the OpenStack services, clients, libs and their
dependencies self-contained in it's repositories.
We have had users that were impacted by sudden updates from EPEL
when it was enabled because EPEL provided a more up-to-date version.
Packages may also be found in both the delorean and delorean-deps
repositories. yum-plugin-priorities will ensure the right package
candidates are chosen for installation.

Change-Id: I043ec1f60381dc7f5baab5f320ed5f1edde8ae82
Related-bug: https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1284978
Closes-bug: #1520620

commit_message:
bump minimum version of cliff

openstackclient no longer uses cliff-tablib and depends on
functionality specific to cliff 1.15.0

Change-Id: I51dd2dea9b6020bf6e8ca078bdda16bd2ee8a23c
Closes-Bug: 1510546

commit_message:
Remove lbaasv2-dsvm-minimal job from running on doc changes

Doc changes in the gate are running
gate-neutron-lbaasv2-dsvm-minimal, which (being a long running job)
is contrary to the current filters for doc jobs, so extend
the filtering string to cover booth lbaasv1 and lbaasv2 explicitly

Change-Id: I84e020bc4ee2e0f0b519a27fe8436467dc4c28e4
Signed-off-by: Ryan Moats <rmoats@us.ibm.com>

commit_message:
Add translations bones

The build guts around translations are missing, which means pbr does not
implement the Project Testing Interface. Although it has not been
defined what, if any, strings need to be translated, make the repo have
the sufficient pieces to handle translating things and the PTI.

Change-Id: I80945910861d84d808a2814bcbfad9945e6ea723
Closes-Bug: #1189117

this is awesome'}, {'account_id': 1653, 'date': '2015-09-20 09:56:25.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review+2'}, {'account_id': 7118, 'date': '2015-09-21 01:17:05.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

-1 because we should include even a minimal test-case (tests/test_functions.sh probably)

This is a fun hack ... but putting in a gate-breaking time-bomb seems like, well, not a good idea.  

By Murphy's law, it will happen at a bad time and cause unintended flow-on affects.  Although you can argue that we (people related to upstream infra) can fix the gate quickly by pushing through a change, there's plenty of external users that don't update every second and have other "interesting" setups; we should attempt to minimise their pain.

Putting out a warning in the middle of thousands of lines of devstack log file is as good as doing nothing, I admit.

Maybe a compromise is to move the log messages for timed-out work-arounds into a separate log file?  This way they're easy to find, but we're not going to shoot ourselves in the foot.'}, {'account_id': 2750, 'date': '2015-09-22 11:36:00.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

Honestly, I'd rather move to a standard comment format for workarounds with timeboxing, and generate a report on those. It's all well and good to assume a timebomb in the future is going to be motivation to get things done, but life happens."}, {'account_id': 2, 'date': '2015-11-29 00:50:34.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

Add a timebox function

timebox is a way to mark workarounds so that we don't forget to come
back and address them.

commit_message:
[doc] Update _i18n.py example to pass pep8

It would be nice if the _i18n.py example can be copy-and-paste
to myapp/_i18n.py without pep8 errors.

Change-Id: I9ff4174ba1cac56c8b20ba572757fb54baa1e9bb

[{'created': '2015-11-25 15:53:29.000000000', 'message': 'Remove netaddr useless requirement

This patch cleans up the requirement list to remove netaddr module
that is not used anymore directly by cinder.

commit_message:
Remove netaddr useless requirement

This patch cleans up the requirement list to remove netaddr module
that is not used anymore directly by cinder.

Change-Id: I0d0efbf26fb43e94f2ccc1a62edaba6f2b13f27e

commit_message:
Fix InstanceLocalityFilter scheduler filter

Commit I51254e20151fe1d6771897e64a8d0bdf2d674d03 introduces new error:
We use novaclient extensions instead of Nova API extensions. In such
case, InstanceLocalityFilter won't find Nova ExtendedServerAttributes
extension and will raise CinderException.

This patch fixes novaclient usage in a right way.

Change-Id: I36fb67d597b7848dd4796ea672bc573a570677e8
Closes-Bug: #1517431

[{'created': '2015-09-25 19:33:21.000000000', 'message': 'Update OCF stop actions to use procfs

This change updates the OCF scripts that currently kill a process to
check procfs to ensure the process actually has stopped. Additionally
this change adds a default retry of 5 times with a 2 second sleep
between sending SIGTERM signals to the processes. If the SIGTERM does
not work, a SIGKILL will also be tried 5 times with a 2 second sleep
before erroring.

Change-Id: I8dcc1c37d17068a9c29480b886d4f1a051f28894
Closes-Bug: 1425579

'}, {'created': '2015-09-29 20:52:25.000000000', 'message': 'Update OCF stop actions to use procfs

This change adds a set of fuel functions that can be used to stop
processes using a pid file or a pid. These functions allow for the same
method of stopping processes to be used by all ocf scripts. The process
stopping logic leverages procfs to check to make sure the process has
been stopped.

This change adds a default retry of 5 times with a 2 second sleep
between sending SIGTERM signals to the processes. This retry count is
dynamic based on the timeout for the stopping command. If the SIGTERM
does not work, a SIGKILL will also be tried one time.

Change-Id: I8dcc1c37d17068a9c29480b886d4f1a051f28894
Closes-Bug: 1425579

commit_message:
Update OCF stop actions to use procfs

This change adds a set of fuel functions that can be used to stop
processes using a pid file or a pid. These functions allow for the same
method of stopping processes to be used by all ocf scripts. The process
stopping logic leverages procfs to check to make sure the process has
been stopped.

This change adds a default retry of 5 times with a 2 second sleep
between sending SIGTERM signals to the processes. This retry count is
dynamic based on the timeout for the stopping command. If the SIGTERM
does not work, a SIGKILL will also be tried one time.

This change does not include the ocf script for rabbitmq as that is the
upstream version and won't be leveraging the ocf-fuel-funcs library.

This change does not include the ocf script for mysql as that needs
further work.

Change-Id: I8dcc1c37d17068a9c29480b886d4f1a051f28894
Partial-Bug: 1425579

commit_message:
Install correct version of packages on CentOS7

In CentOS7 we will use one version of ruby (ruby 2.0),
thus we should correct package names to be installed.

Blueprint: master-on-centos7

Compatible with CentOS6 master node

Change-Id: Ia79c96a99e00ab82e2117c576f2dbb1d44e14e45

commit_message:
Add Cinder Block Device role

This commit adds a new role for Cinder Storage - Cinder Block
Device role.

Also added new function for getting list of disks, which are
allocated for some role.

Added a new noop test for covering new role.

blueprint cinder-block-device-driver
Depends-On: I0279adffc3866608109efd23845ef2aa365e0704

Change-Id: Ic574f0ea484ac11cfceef2a8e836ca5432084d58

commit_message:
Enable dnsmasq service autostart

Being a systemd-controlled service dnsmasq should be configured
to start automatically.

Blueprint: master-on-centos7

Is compatible with CentOS6 master node

Change-Id: I7cd68a0a67a057d49e0254d58dd0ba5916852e3b

commit_message:
Implement tunable Horizon/Apache processes/threads overrides

This patch introduces an override for the number of Apache processes
and threads for Horizon:
 - horizon_wsgi_processes
 - horizon_wsgi_threads

The values may be set in /etc/openstack_deploy/user_variables.yml
and if they are unset, half the number of available vCPU's will be
used instead.

Implements: blueprint gate-split
Change-Id: Ie608ef66b8979a466e72c6085c9afa6ab95cc6ff
(cherry picked from commit 58205d76043e5ffbaf7475945b364448705f7bfa)

commit_message:
Improve message of the teardown.sh

Currently the teardown doesn't care about destroy other lxc
containers and destroys everything.
Same for logical volumes in the lxc volume group.

This tweaks the message to make it more clear.

Closes-Bug: #1518492

Change-Id: If8bbd9c8b6cea4d18ad982ee676e0480a88a1a4e
(cherry picked from commit 96b33d6d1c55e9d9bc723f415d1a3d8561823d13)

commit_message:
Initialize freezer-scheduler with insecure mode for keystone v3

Add verify and insecure flags for freezer scheduler and apiclient in order to handle
insecure connections when keystone and freezer-api are available through https
Add support for keystone v2 and v3 in the windows scheduler
Add explicit parameters to apiclient for v3 connections

Change-Id: Ib950c85e3d8d2b192ec7ba60e4fe5641202d2960

Windows scheduler now points to keystone v3 endpoints

keystone v2.0 endpoints are being deprecated, now the scheduler only points to v3
on windows

commit_message:
LOG.exception should be mocked in unit test

There is a call to LOG.exception in the exception block
(except putils.ProcessExecutionError).

In the unit test, this exception is mocked:
mock_open.side_effect = putils.ProcessExecutionError
mock_execute.side_effect = putils.ProcessExecutionError.
When trying to print the message using LOG.exception that
is not in a real exception block, it throws additional exception.

All patches to stable/liberty are blocked by this unit test
failure. See this patch here:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/249358/

This bug was fixed in the trunk as part of porting the test
to python3. This fix was manually cherry-picked from the
following commit because that commit also had other changes:
https://github.com/openstack/cinder/commit/
7d849b5da48a4edb29db288c041b945cc34f667a

Change-Id: I2960ac83ee772ce2b4bda3de7eb76789e6f1a0ac
Closes-Bug: #1519978

commit_message:
simplify collector cache

we can avoid the overhead of deep copying a dict for each resource.
we can also avoid the overhead of even building a comparable hash
if the cache doesn't have the key to begin with.

Change-Id: Ie4e4a19707cab411bc93fd864aa7f68f49df6c1b

commit_message:
clean up integration test urls

the endpoints for aodh, ceilometer and gnocchi end with trailing
slash. because of that, our tests are calling <endpoint>//<path>.
this works but is technically incorrect. this patch cleans it up.

Change-Id: Ieed46c38fff4e7ea86f0f5eeab105c70b6249003

slash. because of that, our tests are calling <endpoint>//<path>.

commit_message:
clean up integration test urls

the endpoints for aodh, ceilometer and gnocchi end with trailing
slash. because of that, our tests are calling <endpoint>//<path>.
this works but is technically incorrect. this patch cleans it up.

Change-Id: Ia3f9c628659c7e215fef84886a15d30895df79fe

commit_message:
Update toctree of neutron document

* Display more contents in the top page.
  It is useful to access various things from the top page.
  The contents after this change looks reasonable.
* Remove "Indices and tables" section in policies and stadium index.
  They are unnecessary.

Change-Id: I49a966ce96af107c6f17f4caa73f9a634db37e18

commit_message:
IPAM: fix 'enable-dhcp' with internal driver

Commit 0c1f96ad5a6606c1205bd50ea944c3a383892cde broke the ipam
internal driver. The base plugin should only call the ipam interface
and not invoke the IPallocation data model.

The code that validated that the subnet had one free IP address was
removed. This would not guarantee that a port would indeed be free,
that is, a parallel operation could have created a port on the subnet
during this check.

Closes-bug: #1514810

Conflicts:
	neutron/db/db_base_plugin_v2.py

Change-Id: I4d7ecb985762a8eef39cb2f22f210b4899f1a22e
(cherry picked from commit 8d8444aa0ce0e6db1ebbc922311ec1eef546f2fe)

commit_message:
Make policy-update return 400 instead of 404

When the specified policy or the policy is not attached, we return a 400
(bad request) instead of a 404 error.

Change-Id: Ie04ceb7420db697d97f461c6a84d19e72ae620ee
Partial-Bug: #1518209

commit_message:
Revert "Add Scality SRB driver"

The Scality SRB kernel-driver is being re-designed to optimize for
specific workloads, which are (initially) not compatible with VM-style
block device access. Not to confuse users, we believe it's advisable to
remove the Cinder SRB driver in the meantime.

This reverts commit a23f17f8cebe5e1e57f675aedf6272257257d1b7.

Some references to the SRB driver and test modules added in later
commits are removed as well.

Conflicts:
        cinder/tests/unit/test_srb.py
        cinder/volume/drivers/srb.py
        etc/cinder/rootwrap.d/volume.filters

See: 2f9e4163f42ae5246fd997b9f35e16d3d97be54f
See: 3fda737f53824170bd59eb6e8ce2e991c89c3c1d

Change-Id: Ic9d79b09363ef904932128f63371ba01a15c5d31

commit_message:
Implement tunable heat api and engine worker overrides

This patch introduces an override for the number of Heat engine and
Heat API workers:
 - heat_engine_workers
 - heat_api_workers

The values may be set in /etc/openstack_deploy/user_variables.yml
and if they are unset, half the number of available vCPU's will be
used instead.

Implements: blueprint gate-split
Change-Id: I1ecb4951fe8336d9ef86ef9d5c8c21105a299096
(cherry picked from commit 7d8105ed5531efab1dddf37845e732d4c66ad01e)

commit_message:
ScaleIO extend volume round up capacity

ScaleIO only supports volumes with a granularity of 8 GB.
In extend volume, we need to round up the volume to the
nearest size that is a granularity of 8 GBs.

Change-Id: I1d1340fa6d31f89a0c166e66c7c84583dbfe5102
Closes-Bug: #1519613

commit_message:
Fix engine service function's decorator

There are xyz_find functions decorated today though they are not invoked
directly from RPC client. These functions should not be decorated or
else the redundant decoration is making exception handling pretty hard
to debug.

Change-Id: Id2a483ba856c6d134f8dfc7a71db68643d751a35

commit_message:
Docs: specify --docker-volume-size for swarm bay

If this option is not specified, the default is 25GB which is too big
to fail the stack creation.

Change-Id: I75fca1ab150f2df76c2464647c3d4f73dd7463f7
Closes-Bug: #1520308

commit_message:
fix exceptions.from_response() parameter

The exceptions.from_response() takes 'method' as it's second param.
see:
python-magnumclient/magnumclient/openstack/common/apiclient/exceptions.py
def from_response(response, method, url):
    xxx

Change-Id: I66afa28ee3e80dc50156c790af4b03afac2292c4

commit_message:
{pg,my}sql: fix AttributeError on connection failure

If connection fails to be established, the acquired attribute does not
exist and then you see warning such has:

Exception AttributeError: "'MySQLLock' object has no attribute 'acquired'" in
<bound method MySQLLock.__del__ of <tooz.drivers.mysql.MySQLLock object at 0x7f79479056d0>>

Change-Id: Id61775483c91ba4127d9dd8cb56d6629a51d7081

commit_message:
Added allow_async property

In Nova we need a decorator that is READER by default
but can be used as ASYNC if asynchronous session is started before.

Co-Authored-By: Sergey Nikitin <snikitin@mirantis.com>

Change-Id: I0c0f332d87bf6b1213c800763918340b1e226934

Actually I found this issue when I'm working on a Congress BP.

Congress nova driver will query nova instances in fixed interval by using novaclient, and check whether some changes occur on the instance, like: status, fixed-ip and so on. I can't use obj1 == obj2 to check, because even if the instance's status is changed from ACTIVE to PAUSED, the result still is True.

I don't know whether other services depend the compare method obj1 == obj2, but I think method '==' should be a normal usage."}, {'account_id': 9796, 'date': '2015-11-11 05:24:22.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

commit_message:
Fix Resource.__eq__ mismatch semantics of object equal

The __eq__ of apiclient.base.Resource will return True,
if the two objects have same id, even if they have different
other attributes value. The behavior is weird and don't
match the semantics of object equal. The objects that have
different value should be different objects.

Fix this issue and add some test cases in this patch.

Change-Id: I92ce3af0a51befd9cf04ea779079eef95d89606f
Closes-Bug: #1499369

commit_message:
Virtual instance rescue with stable disk devices

This will provide the ability to indicate that the rescue disk image
should be attached as a transient disk device (ie USB stick), so that
existing storage attached to an instance doesn't change its device
address during rescue mode.

Change-Id: Ib7163ec85c303e7256a2cc353989e91628fff475
Blueprint: virt-rescue-stable-disk-devices

commit_message:
Need a way to list compute node metric names

Proposes a way to list compute node metric names by adding a new
nova-manage command.

APIImpact: new API to list compute node metric names

Implements: blueprint compute-node-metrics-api
Change-Id: I9638f126dd2fd8bd9afec095010784daef611e9a

commit_message:
Fix request body of pause-vm-during-live-migration

The api-wg guideline mentions
 "Field names should use snake_case style, not CamelCase or
  MixedCase style."

So hyphens are not good in a request body.
This patch fixes the body before the implementation.

commit_message:
Last sync to Manila from oslo-incubator

Oslo incubator is going away, and we cannot use the sync script
to copy the incubator files to Manila one last time because at
least one file has changed in Manila since the last sync.  This
commit includes the remaining changes which we do want.  The files
are consistent with the oslo-incubator master branch as of commit
305c2b0d52d387c0039e3b3021c4de27e85cd175.

Change-Id: Ib880a0108e4a567ebe39aa1ada7f872c63a818f1

[{'created': '2015-10-02 11:39:35.000000000', 'message': 'Virt image properties boot time override

This extends the Nova boot API so that it is possible to override any
image metadata properties at instance creation time. This avoids the
need to upload the same image to glance multiple times in order to
set slightly different properties for special use cases.

Change-Id: I47e3df44cd868b965ef2b6cffad509b2895cb02a
Blueprint: virt-image-props-boot-override
'}, {'created': '2015-10-13 11:48:06.000000000', 'message': 'Virt image properties boot time override

This extends the Nova boot API so that it is possible to override any
image metadata properties at instance creation time. This avoids the
need to upload the same image to glance multiple times in order to
set slightly different properties for special use cases.

commit_message:
Virt image properties boot time override

This extends the Nova boot API so that it is possible to override any
image metadata properties at instance creation time. This avoids the
need to upload the same image to glance multiple times in order to
set slightly different properties for special use cases.

APIImpact
Blueprint: virt-image-props-boot-override
Change-Id: I47e3df44cd868b965ef2b6cffad509b2895cb02a

commit_message:
[install] Updates the keystone install

This patch updates the commands made by the postinst of Keystone,
as the package moved to use the Keystone v3 API.

Note that still missing is the use of Apache instead of the
eventlet setup for Keystone. Please bare with me, and accept
this as an incremental step, as this will come later on.

Change-Id: I497f671b4f96d700be189d8e363a8c75c513e207

commit_message:
deprecate timeutils.total_seconds()

Because datetime.timedelta doesn't have method total_seconds in
Python2.6, we use timeutils.total_seconds() to calculate it manually.
Now we dropped Python 2.6, and this method will be deprecated in
oslo.utils. According to patch https://review.openstack.org/#/c/248590/,
we should use datetime.timedelta.total_seconds() instead of
timeutils.total_seconds().

Change-Id: I5a4957ba863d1df332367088140517fd89986147

commit_message:
WIP Barbican Client JSON Validation

This patch will allow for the validation of JSON files which will
be used to generate Secrets, Orders, Containers, ACLs. This patch
is a WORK IN PROGRESS and only contains a testcase for validation
of Secrets in test_utils. Reviews are welcome.

Change-Id: I006ec71e98d05b718eca197102254096e36aeca1
Implements: blueprint object-creation-through-json

commit_message:
Use neutron._i18n instead of neutron.i18n

It is suggested to use _i18n.py per oslo.i18n document.
http://docs.openstack.org/developer/oslo.i18n/usage.html

* Add neutron._i18n.py
* Change all neutron modules to consume the new _i18n.py

Note that neutron.i18n is being used in various neutron
subprojects and it will be removed after cleanup in subprojects
has been completed.

tox.ini [hacking] import_exceptions contains only neutron._i18n.
This ensures no import of neutron.i18n happens in neutron repo.
neutron.i18n will be removed after subproject cleanup.

Partial-Bug: #1519493
Change-Id: I739205248bd57b4c43dc5438f8dfed971d0f9486

commit_message:
Stop configure_diskspace from using small partitions

configure_diskspace will attempt to use a small partition
(<MIN_LXC_VG_SIZE_B) if it does not find either a VG or
existing mount point.

The VG creation code checks for minimum size, but the final fall back
that creates a partition does not.

Change-Id: I4942321f1253e7ae4773d04d28122c90c91f39a0
Closes-Bug: 1488670

commit_message:
Don't drop vcns tables that may not exist

If one of the vcns tables doesn't exist, the neutron-db-manage
execution of 57086602ca0a_scrap_nsx_adv_svcs_models.py fails.

There should be a check for the existence of the table prior to
dropping.

Closes-bug: #1452066

Change-Id: I42ca838b9da063a44c22860e2ec94217c0c38595

commit_message:
Fix tenant_network test

The test_tenant_network.test_network_index_with_default_net was
actually passing as a false positive.  The default name of the
default network is "default", so this network never matched "1",
so fake_network_api_get_all never returned default networks.

The default network should not have a cidr value.

And finally some of the assertEquals were improperly ordered as
(actual, expected).

Change-Id: Ia710ba1aefdd1db130b1ab161c2ec2fb60336212

commit_message:
add neutron client support

For good user experience, we should validate if Baymodel's network
is existed in Bay creation. Currently in Magnum there is no Neutron
client support. Neutron client is added for network related
resources validation.

Change-Id: I5668e3b67b8addbff14c7f859a5124c099f35a88
Patially-Implements: blueprint api-parameter-validation

commit_message:
Add "INACTIVE" into "status" for firewall res params

If user creates a firewall with no "router_ids", the firewall status is set
"INACTIVE".  This commit adds "INACTIVE" into "status" param.

Change-Id: Ied77f4313a483e666e5e323522d4bc1b8a248908
Closes-Bug: #1518698

commit_message:
Updated appropriate type values for Cinder-v2-volumeactions APIs

The os-attach, os-unmanage, os-force_detach,
os-set_image_metadata, os-unset_image_metadata, and metadata
parameters of the volume v2 API are type "dict" and not "string".

(df) Also, updated ID to UUID, where appropriate.

Change-Id: Idae0832d3753b06646a60590afae69c924fa755a
Closes-Bug: #1519166

commit_message:
Update appropriate types for parameters of Cinder-v2-API's

The parameter "metadata" is a "dict" type, but given as
"string" type, so it is replaced with "dict"
The parameter attachments is a "list" type but given as
"dict" type, so it is replaced with "list"

Change-Id: I7a89561b875737feca7ef90b2b10a7fa50d21538
Closes-Bug: #1519162

There is a typo on the error message that is shown when the user
tries to increase the user quota limit above the tenant quota
limit. This patch changes the error message from:
"Quota limit must less than %s."
to:

Closes-bug: #1516997

commit_message:
Fix typo on quota limit error message

There is a typo on the error message that is shown when the user
tries to increase the user quota limit above the tenant quota
limit. This patch changes the error message from:
"Quota limit must less than %s."
to:
"Quota limit must be less than %s."

Change-Id: I713db2a3e053ab9beac4561be8f236aa8a1fc194
Closes-bug: #1516997

commit_message:
Add "firewall" and "firewalls" into FWaaS API

This commit adds "firewall" and "firewalls" into following APIs.

  * POST/PUT /v2.0/fw/firewalls
    "firewall"(xsd:dict)  : Request/Response params
  * GET /v2.0/fw/firewalls
    "firewalls"(xsd:list) : Response params

Change-Id: I39f0e89f2289c4aa32387e2cceba0a0d2a7fd03e
Closes-Bug: #1518697

commit_message:
Change id type from uuid to string

For GET os-certificates request's request id param,
it's not a uuid, it's a string; and only 'root' is
valid input string now.

Change-Id: I0def27e6ca706d239b374344af868c9673011eeb
Partial-Bug: #1515222

commit_message:
Add GET /v2.1/tenant_id/os-floating-ips/id method

this method is enabled by nova api but not in the doc
so add it.

(df) Update the floating IP samples
(df) Clarify the other floating IP methods
(df) Make language for server actions, including floating IP actions,
consistent

Change-Id: I3b97964bb999063f97a17e26a3d755bef133ef32
Partial-Bug: #1515222

commit_message:
Deprecate timeutils.total_seconds()

According to patch https://review.openstack.org/#/c/248590/ ,
we need to use datetime.timedelta.total_seconds() instead of
timeutils.total_seconds() which will be deprecated in oslo.utils.

Change-Id: If2369974a226c492ee996a2d23f09c6bcb495665

commit_message:
Use oslo_utils encodeutils and strutils

With oslo-incubator being deprecated, move
our use of strutils to oslo_utils.

This leaves in place the use of oslo-incubator's
strutils by other oslo-incubator modules for now.

Change-Id: Ic4e50060b42aeca9d1e54424a8a3a123140fbf2a

commit_message:
Implement new Liberty default for Neutron rpc_workers

The default number of Neutron rpc_workers has changed in Liberty from 0
to 1. This patches changes the default to this value, as the default of 0
results in a very high number of workers.

Implements: blueprint gate-split
Implements: blueprint liberty-release
Change-Id: I31ebbbbb10e260b2895aa5d55d3716136dbffd90
(cherry picked from commit ccf83be6654c9a49e32205bc1697502a7c7a6320)

commit_message:
bump requests to 2.8.1

in requests < 2.8.0, there is a bug where connections are not
returned to the pool and thus the connection pool becomes exhausted.
this is fixed as of 2.8.0

this is required for ceilometer and gnocchiclient.

Change-Id: I1326dbef072ca7a6155c9fd5771ec6d8f51a1dc3
see: https://github.com/kennethreitz/requests/issues/2687

commit_message:
Adds some more considerations for rel notes update

There were some comments mentioned in
I2ffe427b12b456a3ebbdaacfacb8db49f25a47c6 that are included in this
change.

It also changes the copyright right from Searchlight Developers to
OpenStack Foundation, with the latter being a legaly represented entity.

Change-Id: If96641ad4fb59747c091efd48f7e4a97b62050ca

commit_message:
Implement tunable Ceilometer workers

This patch introduces an override for the number of Ceilometer workers:
 - ceilometer_api_workers
 - ceilometer_collector_workers
 - ceilometer_notification_workers

The values may be set in /etc/openstack_deploy/user_variables.yml
and if they are unset, half the number of available vCPU's will be
used instead.

Backport Note:
The var locations were changed in the following patch and apply to
Liberty+ only:
 - https://review.openstack.org/209333

Implements: blueprint gate-split
Change-Id: I126d735b737237cde27dde8a864e945d037e2e4a
(cherry picked from commit a8cc6b473796de5c2b1c38186c6537d5b91e7514)

commit_message:
firstapp - move libcloud sec5 to sample file

The Block Storage Section, originally written for libcloud
now has support for other SDKs. libcloud should be treated
the same as other SDKs, so this patch simply moves the
code samples into a dedicated file, as per the per all
other sections.

Change-Id: Ide9e8f29aec37b0410d133549679406ecdc0cce2

commit_message:
Added the jclouds scaling out code sample

Added a scaling out code sample for jclouds and modified the
scaling out chapter to reference it.

Also modified the build so that the jclouds draft documentation
is now generated so that we can see the code appear in context.

Change-Id: Iaf9ee952e008bdb68e52717524de723597da0690
Partial-Bug: #1449330

commit_message:
Swarm: Split swarm.yaml to swarmcluster.yaml and swarmmaster.yaml

Would like to make swarm much more similar with k8s.

This patch is the preparation of supporting Swarm HA mode:
1. Refactor swarm.yaml to swarmcluster.yaml and swarmmaster.yaml
2. Add api_pool, LB in front of swarm master node.
3. Add etcd_pool

After this change:

Swarm bay will update the fileds of 'master_addresses'.

P.S. notes Swarm HA is not supported yet, master_addresses will be only 1
ip address.

Partially implements: blueprint swarm-high-availability
Change-Id: Ib6346bfd5a7ad0ef2226a6e6bc98b0ad46e577cb

commit_message:
VMware: Validate extra spec opt vmware:clone_type

This patch validates the value of extra spec option 'vmware:clone_type'.
It raises an exception if the value is invalid.

Change-Id: Idab59a090184e1ea1446e9e9ed18c753d5c803cc
Closes-Bug: #1288254

This introduces 2 variables:
``horizon_site_name`` and ``horizon_custom_uploads``.

The former needs to set with a string. It will edit the

files that the deployer wants to upload.

horizon_custom_uploads:

    src: '/etc/openstack_deploy/files/logo.png'
    dest: "{{ horizon_lib_dir }}/openstack_dashboard/static/dashboard/img/logo.png"

    src: '/etc/openstack_deploy/files/logo-splash.png'
    dest: "{{ horizon_lib_dir }}/openstack_dashboard/static/dashboard/img/logo-splash.png"

You'll overwrite the logo and logo-splash file on the dest folder
on the horizon node with the files stored on the deployment node
in the src folder.

commit_message:
Allow Horizon Custom Branding

This introduces 2 variables:
``horizon_site_name`` and ``horizon_custom_uploads``.

The former needs to set with a string. It will edit the
local settings of horizon to add the cloud's name.

The latter is a dict, that contains path to source and destination
files that the deployer wants to upload.
For example, if setting the dict as followed:

horizon_custom_uploads:
  logo:
    src: '/etc/openstack_deploy/files/logo.png'
    dest: "img/logo.png"
  logosplash:
    src: '/etc/openstack_deploy/files/logo-splash.png'
    dest: "img/logo-splash.png"

You'll overwrite the img/logo.png and img/logo-splash.png files
on the horizon nodes (inside their folder
"{{ horizon_lib_dir }}/openstack_dashboard/static/dashboard/")
with the files stored on the deployment node at the src location.

Change-Id: I1a74e74968d09f6e299dbd965f9c87368c4d646c

commit_message:
Optimise the workers used for all services for the AIO

The current default number of worker threads for the AIO consumes too many
resources, resulting in gate check failures.

This patch implements a set of sane defaults for the AIO, reducing the
number of workers for most services to 2.

Implements: blueprint gate-split
Change-Id: I553c6aa8711fa85434547585d3a56cca47539fa0
(cherry picked from commit 8e52fbb2f2c99d6b55f7dc10a3812276ce581301)

commit_message:
NFS setup for live-migration job

This patch add nfs shared storage for ephemerals
and run tempest tests again.
This is used in the gate-tempest-dsvm-multinode-live-migration job
which is run on the experimental queue only right now.

Change-Id: Ief89e614dd0cb218ab816da506e627b01f2ec5c1

commit_message:
Simplified boolean variable check

Currently 'test_list' variable is being checked
for empty list like 'if test_list == []:'.
The more standard approach is like 'if not test_list:'.

TrivialFix

Change-Id: I0b389c11b992c93529b305b1ebce6b181f9a9a30

commit_message:
Source installation in virtualenv

Use virtualenv for installation of OpenStack projects and
dependencies to avoid conflicts with Python libraries installed
by non-OpenStack binary packages.

Change-Id: I21ecd673b2e93335b1d3dd4e279e940c9d694c3c
Implements: blueprint virtualenv

commit_message:
Return empty PciDevicePoolList obj instead of None

If a ComputeNode object has its pci_device_pools field set to an empty
PciDevicePoolList object and then that node object is saved via the
save() method, the pci_device_pools field of the same object is changed
to None due to the from_pci_stats() returning None if pci_stats is None.
The fix is to return an empty PciDevicePoolList instead of None,
ensuring that calling save() does not have this unintended side effect.

Closes-Bug: #1492342
Change-Id: I7b5a3ed24d137646579fc4534c71a2bc6baa8ca6

commit_message:
make release_from_yaml.py figure out the deliverable files for us

Change the args to release_from_yaml.py so that if no deliverable files
are provided it looks at the git history of the releases repository to
find the files changed in the most recent commit.

Call release.sh for each of the files given (or discovered) instead of
just a single file.

Change-Id: I7dc392df1d6b9c7e4e1d4d85c9690ee9480e8c31

commit_message:
fix error handling and bug reporting in release script

After the tag is pushed, we don't want to die with an error if we can't
update the bug reports, so turn off the -e shell flag.

We have to check for the previous tag before we add the new one, because
the logic for finding the last tag assumes the new one is not there yet.

Change-Id: If2ac25b8bd96e4e0c5b90016a3c40d43733ab849

commit_message:
Release tagging automation

This change implements the Mitaka-style release process.

The new release_from_yaml.py is called (manually for the moment)
when a deliverable release request is merged in openstack/releases.

It calls release.sh to tag repositories in that deliverable:
- applying the tag if it does not exist
- adding comments referencing the release to Launchpad for bugs
  mentioned ("Closes-Bug") in git commit messages since last tag

add_comment.py is the launchpadlib script handling that last action.

Change-Id: I40b5f5957ff765d2c582d126b940260bb47547e8

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-11-25 16:20:15.000000000', 'message': "Change AIO bootstrap disk preparation

This implements a change in the AIO disk preparation in the hope that
it will result in less Gate failures (due to the OS disk running low)
and will increase the flexibility slightly for dev/test purposes.

This introduces the following new environment variables:

 - BOOTSTRAP_AIO_DIR
   A data directory for the AIO's loopback disks. This was previously
   hard coded to '/opt'.
 - DATA_DISK_DEVICE
   If there is a large enough secondary disk available, the bootstrap
   script will repartition it, format it and mount it at
   BOOTSTRAP_AIO_DIR.
   If you wish to specify which disk to use, then this var may be set.

This also changes the following environment variable:
 - MIN_LXC_VG_SIZE_GB -> MIN_DISK_SIZE_GB
   This represents the smallest disk size required (in GB) which may
   be repurposed by the bootstrap script.

This patch also makes some minor optimisations in some of the grep
statements relating to the loopback disks.

The new process implements the following major changes:

 - The LXC containers will share BOOTSTRAP_AIO_DIR with the loopback
   disks for cinder-volume, swift, swap and nova.
 - The nova instances will now be built onto a sparse loopback disk
   mounted at /var/lib/nova/instances. This is specifically due to
   issues with that directory being on the root disk for gate tests
   and the root disks are too small to support instance creation.
 - LXC containers will always use sparse files, unless the end-user
   sets up their own lxc vg.

Change-Id: I96b0c787ed4b6bb01a629a7899bea581fb39be4f

Change-Id: I96b0c787ed4b6bb01a629a7899bea581fb39be4f"}, {'created': '2015-11-26 12:20:04.000000000', 'message': "Change AIO bootstrap disk preparation

This implements a change in the AIO disk preparation in the hope that
it will result in less Gate failures (due to the OS disk running low)
and will increase the flexibility slightly for dev/test purposes.

This introduces the following new environment variables:

 - BOOTSTRAP_AIO_DIR
   A data directory for the AIO's loopback disks. This was previously
   hard coded to '/opt' and is now set to '/openstack'.
 - DATA_DISK_DEVICE
   If there is a large enough secondary disk available, the bootstrap
   script will repartition it, format it and mount it at
   BOOTSTRAP_AIO_DIR.
   If you wish to specify which disk to use, then this var may be set.

This also changes the following environment variable:
 - MIN_LXC_VG_SIZE_GB -> MIN_DISK_SIZE_GB
   This represents the smallest disk size required (in GB) which may
   be repurposed by the bootstrap script. This size is set to 80G by
   default.

This patch also makes some minor optimisations in some of the grep
statements relating to the loopback disks and moves some of the gate
check script actions to accommodate the reparitioning of /openstack
which is where the gate check logs are held.

The new process implements the following major changes:

 - The BOOTSTRAP_AIO_DIR contains the loopback disks for
   cinder-volume, swift, swap and nova.
 - /var/lib/lxc will always be a normal ext4 partition - it used to
   be done this way in RAX Cloud and setup as a LVM VG in HP Cloud.
 - LXC containers will always use sparse files, unless the end-user
   sets up their own lxc vg.
 - The nova instances will now be built onto a sparse loopback disk
   mounted at /var/lib/nova/instances. This is specifically due to
   issues with that directory being on the root disk for gate tests
   and the root disks are too small to support instance creation.
 - The /openstack directory will be setup as a partition on the
   second disk. As this directory holds variable data this is deemend
   more appropriate for long running AIO testing and development.

Implements: blueprint gate-split
Change-Id: I96b0c787ed4b6bb01a629a7899bea581fb39be4f

   A data directory for the AIO's loopback disks. This was previously
   hard coded to '/opt' and is now set to '/openstack'.
 - DATA_DISK_DEVICE
   If there is a large enough secondary disk available, the bootstrap
   script will repartition it, format it and mount it at
   BOOTSTRAP_AIO_DIR.
   If you wish to specify which disk to use, then this var may be set.

This also changes the following environment variable:
 - MIN_LXC_VG_SIZE_GB -> MIN_DISK_SIZE_GB
   This represents the smallest disk size required (in GB) which may
   be repurposed by the bootstrap script. This size is set to 80G by
   default.

This patch also makes some minor optimisations in some of the grep
statements relating to the loopback disks and moves some of the gate
check script actions to accommodate the reparitioning of /openstack
which is where the gate check logs are held.

The new process implements the following major changes:

 - The BOOTSTRAP_AIO_DIR contains the loopback disks for
   cinder-volume, swift, swap and nova.
 - /var/lib/lxc will always be a normal ext4 partition - it used to
   be done this way in RAX Cloud and setup as a LVM VG in HP Cloud.
 - LXC containers will always use sparse files, unless the end-user
   sets up their own lxc vg.
 - The nova instances will now be built onto a sparse loopback disk
   mounted at /var/lib/nova/instances. This is specifically due to
   issues with that directory being on the root disk for gate tests
   and the root disks are too small to support instance creation.
 - The /openstack directory will be setup as a partition on the
   second disk. As this directory holds variable data this is deemend
   more appropriate for long running AIO testing and development.

Implements: blueprint gate-split
Change-Id: I96b0c787ed4b6bb01a629a7899bea581fb39be4f

commit_message:
Change AIO bootstrap disk preparation

This implements a change in the AIO disk preparation in the hope that
it will result in less Gate failures (due to the OS disk running low)
and will increase the flexibility slightly for dev/test purposes.

This introduces the following new environment variables:

 - BOOTSTRAP_AIO_DIR
   A data directory for the AIO's loopback disks. This was previously
   hard coded to '/opt' and is now set to '/openstack'.
 - DATA_DISK_DEVICE
   If there is a large enough secondary disk available, the bootstrap
   script will repartition it, format it and mount it at
   BOOTSTRAP_AIO_DIR.
   If you wish to specify which disk to use, then this var may be set.

This also changes the following environment variable:
 - MIN_LXC_VG_SIZE_GB -> MIN_DISK_SIZE_GB
   This represents the smallest disk size required (in GB) which may
   be repurposed by the bootstrap script. This size is set to 80G by
   default.

This patch also makes some minor optimisations in some of the grep
statements relating to the loopback disks and moves some of the gate
check script actions to accommodate the reparitioning of /openstack
which is where the gate check logs are held.

The new process implements the following major changes:

 - The BOOTSTRAP_AIO_DIR contains the loopback disks for
   cinder-volume, swift, swap and nova.
 - /var/lib/lxc will always be a normal ext4 partition - it used to
   be done this way in RAX Cloud and setup as a LVM VG in HP Cloud.
 - LXC containers will always use sparse files, unless the end-user
   sets up their own lxc vg.
 - The nova instances will now be built onto a sparse loopback disk
   mounted at /var/lib/nova/instances. This is specifically due to
   issues with that directory being on the root disk for gate tests
   and the root disks are too small to support instance creation.
 - The /openstack directory will be setup as a partition on the
   second disk. As this directory holds variable data this is deemend
   more appropriate for long running AIO testing and development.

Implements: blueprint gate-split
Change-Id: I96b0c787ed4b6bb01a629a7899bea581fb39be4f

commit_message:
Implement API for openstack configuration

* Add API handlers for openstack configuration to
  browse, upload, download and execute specified
  configurations.

commit_message:
Trivial fix to use constant instead of string for instance action

When referring to instance action, we should use constant defined in
instance_actions.py, but not pure string.

Change-Id: I03b2249e7e5b46bf055d908cc7a0b8beb4dbd748
Signed-off-by: Tang Chen <tangchen@cn.fujitsu.com>

commit_message:
Correct custom group name of Fuel master migration test

- Correct custom group name of the test (as it was refactored
to use template based runner) to have the existing CI job
being able to pick and run the moved test.
- Remove the inital version of the test.

Change-Id: If5bde759d39f2779ea0c9e4b74c1ab94b91774ff
Partial-bug: #1512677

commit_message:
Fix ebtables-version release note

The prelude is defined as "content to appear at
the top of the section for this release.", it's not top of the content
for the following notes. Remove the prelude, there's no way in the
current reno tool to add custom headers.

Change-Id: Iec6b6f1bc8213d602f5db38062fa8efaff501560

commit_message:
Add BetaMax to global requirements

BetaMax is super useful when coupled with requests as a way to
record a session and set of HTTP requests and then replay the actions
within a testing scenario (without needing access to the live web
resources). This will be used in support of a fixture in KeystoneAuth
and OCC so that we can mock out auth-requests and verify that a change
will not break compatibility with active/live clouds.

* Library is maintained by Ian Cordasco
* Library claims compat with python 2.x and 3.x
* Apache 2 License
* Not currently packaged
* Overlaps some with requests-mock but fills a different need


Change-Id: I8787954ab5d0e3963e97c160783301b48ab8299f

commit_message:
devstack config for dogpile cache

Cause devstack to configuration a [cache] section in ceilometer.conf
if CEILOMETER_CACHE_BACKEND is set. Currently set to default to
using dogpile.cache.redis and a redis server on localhost.

This options are not sufficient for generic use as the
"backend_argument"s are not controlled. For general use it is
probably best that tools just modify their local.conf to post config
ceilometer.conf.

Change-Id: I058e60f9440350f80262039171716a3ceb4dec62

Fix typo in 'help' in python-glanceclient

Fix typo `glance --os-image-api-version 1 helpNone` in help
in python-glanceclient.

Change-Id: I21bd7a7a5809e7c5fca4c8df1275321a9014bc6f
Closes-bug: #1506049

commit_message:
Add sleep to CI hooks to avoid races

Manila CI hooks for DHSS=False job with the Generic driver wait for
service instance availability and right after it becomes available
returns control to caller. And caller can run tests with creation of
shares immediately. But, in this case, we can face race conditions when
manila-share service requires some time to inform manila-scheduler.
So, add 'sleep 10' operation to be executed after reaching 'available'
state by service instance.It should be enough to overcome races.

Change-Id: Ie4ae231701edaab319c9012e476d1f63e3806499

commit_message:
Use version convert methods from oslo_utils.versionutils

oslo_utils provide version convert methods in versionutis[1],
so don't need maintain them in nova.

[1]https://github.com/openstack/oslo.utils/blob/master/oslo_utils/versionutils.py

Change-Id: Icbc65ab372379812326265263c2a0b1b20999189

commit_message:
POST certificates returns 200 instead of 201 now

os-certificates POST command returns 200 , not 201 in the code now
we will change it later to 201 in the code but for now
we need to change code to make code and doc consistent.

Change-Id: I0e9bf919a76f85c041d37f7957b537611035459f
Partial-Bug: #1515222

commit_message:
[Manila] Add config ref for the Generic driver

Update the openstack manuals config ref to document the config options
for the Generic driver (Manila project).
Changes:
- Created new table for the Generic driver
- Moved values of 'storage' table to the table with Generic driver as
  it was describing configuration of Cinder client that is used only
  by Generic driver.
- Added flagmappings for new table.
- Remove Generic driver related options from 'share' table.

Change-Id: I52a3f033b98045e3ea250a3e44e69ed346e6037d

commit_message:
Support for httpd 2.4 (CentOS7)

CentOS7 includes httpd package of version 2.4, but existing
template is compatible with 2.2 only.

This commit adds conditional support for httpd 2.4

Blueprint: master-on-centos7

Compatible with CentOS6 master node

Change-Id: I2eb5defbfc219729b991b0e5edf29d6e8eb0fd38

commit_message:
Switch adminurl endpoints to use PublicVirtualIP

This is backward compatible with the way we created endpoints
before, except for the keystone adminurl which is controlled
by the value of KeystoneAdminNetwork from ServiceNetMap.

Change-Id: I1427604a8cc734802b231a6b3fe9a8008b7a64aa
Depends-On: I8874c3c693ab2e447df62f2fad839fd5ad46e761

commit_message:
Convergence: Persist state for stack adopt

Stack create is called internally to complete stack adopt action.
Hence stack adopt will not use stack lock in convergence, so persist
state when state_set is called.

Stack adopt logic is already taken care by convergence.

Change-Id: I2bcfdd7d8b7d9a0ce141ea29ce90253dce0402a8

Remove some dead exception types

Some exception types are now useless after the transport layer is
removed. The patch proposes deletion of them.

James, Sean,
Andrea will be able to provide more information on this. The thing is that we're using Tempest in a SSL enabled environment and we caught already a couple of issues. Having an experimental job with SSL enabled will allow us to probe the feature upstream."}, {'account_id': 1921, 'date': '2015-06-08 07:10:24.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

In Helion we do have SSL enabled and were already hit by regressions on SSL twice.
We have support for SSL in devstack but we're not using it in the gate, so it would be good to start with having an experimental job and see how it behaves. If the execution time / cpu overhead is acceptable it would be good to get SSL enabled at least in some of the gate jobs.

I would say it should be ok to setup an experimental job.
Once we have more data I can bring this up to infra/qa meeting and see if we can reach agreement on enabling SSL."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-07-14 12:13:46.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Verified-1

commit_message:
Enable SSL in devstack for experimental checks.

The purpose of this change is to add an experimental job with SSL enabled and
gather data on how Tempest behaves. In Helion, we're working with SSL enabled
and we hit Tempest issues because it is not tested upstream.

If the analysis of the results of this experimental job show that it may be
good for some gate jobs, we can then have a discussion to reach an agreement
on how enabling SSL in the gate.

Change-Id: I566fccaa9cf9118cf228d04b801ad3191af98c5a

commit_message:
Catch InvalidURL when requesting store size

If location URL looks like scp address:
http://some_address:~/some_image then glance accepts this address
and creates a malformed image.
The problem here is because python http_client lib is trying to
recognize '~' as port but it is not acceptable port name.
The lib generates an InvalidURL exception but this exception is
hidden in one of universal catchers(except Exception).
We need to validate port name (is present before passing it to
http_client lib.

Change-Id: I36dddf7059711fb15ecb1fec4e438daf2bffcb60
Closes-bug: #1485792
(cherry picked from commit caf646af81118af114d38320b83146ff6ae95a07)

commit_message:
AMQP Channel have to be set espacially to 'watcher'

Default channel used is named 'openstack'. But Watcher AMQP topics are
bound to 'watcher' channel. So, on RCPClient init, we have to set
the channel name to 'watcher' for the target.

Change-Id: Ifdbb187f1ee60f898ef0340e0c037891350ce815
Closes-Bug: #1520599

commit_message:
glance: allow explicitly setting store driver

This allows the glance_store driver to be set by overriding
GLANCE_STORE_DRIVER. This is in preparation for functional testing of
individual glance_store drivers.

The previous default behaviour is maintained (uses swift if enabled,
otherwise using filesystem)

Change-Id: I128e31f0740dfe212f32e79c02438b24e78f47d1

commit_message:
Updated the config sample file generation command

Following the update of the project requirements, we should now
use the oslo.config namespace of oslo.log when generating ou
Watcher config sample file.

Change-Id: I7a1f3d555534b40c041b7f042f19fae231b7e80c
Closes-Bug: #1518297

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-10-14 09:29:18.000000000', 'message': "Move from amqp-gem to bunny

Differents:

- separate independent chanel for outgoing report;
- solid way to redeclare already existed queues;
- auto recovery mode in case of network problem by default;
- more solid, modern and simple library for AMQP.

Short words from both gems authors:

amqp gem brings in a fair share of EventMachine complexity which
cannot be fully eliminated. Event loop blocking, writes that
happen at the end of loop tick, uncaught exceptions in event
loop silently killing it: it's not worth the pain unless
you've already deeply invested in EventMachine and
understand how it works.

Closes-Bug: #1498847
Change-Id: I52d005498ccb978ada158bfa64b1c7de1a24e9b0

commit_message:
Move from amqp-gem to bunny

Differents:

- separate independent chanel for outgoing report;
- solid way to redeclare already existed queues;
- auto recovery mode in case of network problem by default;
- more solid, modern and simple library for AMQP.

Also:

- implement asynchronous logger for event callbacks.

Short words from both gems authors:

amqp gem brings in a fair share of EventMachine complexity which
cannot be fully eliminated. Event loop blocking, writes that
happen at the end of loop tick, uncaught exceptions in event
loop silently killing it: it's not worth the pain unless
you've already deeply invested in EventMachine and
understand how it works.

Closes-Bug: #1498847
Closes-Bug: #1487397
Closes-Bug: #1461562
Related-Bug: #1485895
Related-Bug: #1483182

Change-Id: I52d005498ccb978ada158bfa64b1c7de1a24e9b0

commit_message:
Fix a bug of "openstack volume delete"

While multi volumes specified for the osc "openstack volume delete",
only the last volume is deleted.
This patch tries to fix it.

Change-Id: I171b2869f85b29c88fda16eaf5bf163c55795df0
Closes-Bug: #1520541

subject: Fix event emitted on receiving signals
messages:
[{'account_id': 13720, 'date': '2015-11-17 16:19:00.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 7256, 'date': '2015-11-17 16:30:55.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Hrm, so it seems that this would be easier to sort if there was structure to the event details like there is in notifications. That not being the case, I'm not sure there's another way to do this. However, my concern remains that this could potentially break any one consuming these events."}, {'account_id': 4328, 'date': '2015-11-17 18:02:45.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

I'm not sure we can change this - the action for signal events has been "SIGNAL" for as long as I remember, and it's part of our user-visible API surface.

I get the argument that we should perhaps change to the action, with some other means (such as the reason string) showing that it's due to a signal, but IMHO this can't happen until a v2 API.'}, {'account_id': 7256, 'date': '2015-11-17 18:11:35.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

What if we emit two events? Hacky, sure, but would that address both use cases in the meantime?'}, {'account_id': 8246, 'date': '2015-11-17 18:15:37.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

FYI, recorded in V2 API blueprint: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Heat/Blueprints/V2API'}, {'account_id': 4257, 'date': '2015-11-17 18:22:28.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

I'm sure I'm missing something, but this doesn't make any sense to me. If we create a resource and then signal it then the first event is that the CREATE is COMPLETE and the second event is that a SIGNAL happened. To say that the resource is created for a second time is completely untrue and I can't understand why we would want to report it that way.

If you want to know the state before the signal, just look at the previous event."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-11-17 18:41:55.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Verified+1

Build succeeded (check pipeline).

- gate-heat-pep8 http://logs.openstack.org/81/246481/1/check/gate-heat-pep8/275126f/ : SUCCESS in 3m 17s
- gate-heat-docs http://docs-draft.openstack.org/81/246481/1/check/gate-heat-docs/f1a32bb//doc/build/html/ : SUCCESS in 5m 23s
- gate-heat-python27 http://logs.openstack.org/81/246481/1/check/gate-heat-python27/9047ed3/ : SUCCESS in 10m 00s
- gate-heat-python34 http://logs.openstack.org/81/246481/1/check/gate-heat-python34/27b5f18/ : SUCCESS in 10m 47s
- gate-heat-dsvm-functional-orig-mysql http://logs.openstack.org/81/246481/1/check/gate-heat-dsvm-functional-orig-mysql/e9b63a0/ : SUCCESS in 37m 10s
- gate-heat-dsvm-functional-convg-mysql http://logs.openstack.org/81/246481/1/check/gate-heat-dsvm-functional-convg-mysql/8ea3683/ : FAILURE in 1h 02m 04s (non-voting)
- gate-tempest-dsvm-heat http://logs.openstack.org/81/246481/1/check/gate-tempest-dsvm-heat/7e8a813/ : SUCCESS in 33m 29s
- gate-grenade-dsvm-heat http://logs.openstack.org/81/246481/1/check/gate-grenade-dsvm-heat/da8c010/ : SUCCESS in 57m 42s'}, {'account_id': 4328, 'date': '2015-11-17 22:08:22.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

So I think I can see both sides of the argument, e.g "SIGNAL" isn't a stack/resource action, and SIGNAL_COMPLETE isn't a valid stack/resource state, so really we're conflating two things, the action/status of the resource (e.g CREATE_COMPLETE or whatever) and the category of event (which is "hey, signal happened").

I can see why you would find it useful to have both pieces of information in a signal, for example if you're sending a signal clearing a pre-create hook and the resource is UPDATE_COMPLETE or something (IIRC we added validation for that now, but you get my point).

But whatever your view on that, we can't break the existing API by just changing something which has been released several times over, as there's no possible way to determine user impact.

Can someone update the bug with the actual use-case?  It sounds like there is one, but it's not explained in the bug & as Zane mentions there's probably multiple alternative solutions which won't break users that could be suggested.'}, {'account_id': 13720, 'date': '2015-11-27 15:07:24.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

Abandoning, since the consensus is to preserve the current format, and change only in v2'}]

[{'created': '2015-11-17 16:19:00.000000000', 'message': 'Fix event emitted on receiving signals

Resource signals are meaningful in the context of the resource
state, which is defined by resource.action and resource.status.
This patch changes the event emitted when signals are handled so
that it contains the resource action. The nature of the signal
can be deduced from the reason_string that is passed during

Change-Id: Iadb703503b0421ffd10a19b208ecd1cf705c9d88
Closes-Bug: #1517114
'}]
commit_message:
Fix event emitted on receiving signals

Resource signals are meaningful in the context of the resource
state, which is defined by resource.action and resource.status.
This patch changes the event emitted when signals are handled so
that it contains the resource action. The nature of the signal
can be deduced from the reason_string that is passed during
event creation.

Change-Id: Iadb703503b0421ffd10a19b208ecd1cf705c9d88
Closes-Bug: #1517114

commit_message:
Remove the two different auth profiles

Ceph can function just fine generating the keys before the pools have
been created so we can apply the proper permissions to the auth string
ahead of time. This allows us to not require additional steps to add a
cache tier on the fly in the future.

Change-Id: I8214c567fb7c337f95d908c5699d1da922bfa1a6
Closes-Bug: #1518475
(cherry picked from commit 8c1e7061f877c2758b5229a12df771ad0ae8715d)

commit_message:
[networking] Fix L3 HA migration description

* Fix the wrong 'ha' attribute value in the final step
  of "L3 HA to Legacy".
* Improve the description of the impact when setting
  the admin_state_up back to ``True``.
  The previous text seems cut-and-paste'd from
  the similar step and looks confusing.

Change-Id: I79f87e2f66c881f1cff7e2157cbdf2f224dae8a4

commit_message:
AMQP Channel have to be set espacially to 'watcher'.

Default channel used is named 'openstack'. But Watcher AMQP topics are
bound to 'watcher' channel. So, on RCPClient init, we have to set
the channel name to 'watcher' for the target.

Change-Id: Ie80120b2d80a392ffadc537d4d8463c6e366ee0a
Closes-Bug: #1520599

commit_message:
[clients] use keystone.service.list

Method `service_catalog.get_endpoints` of keystoneclient returns not full
informantion about services. For example, it doen't return service name.

`service.list` returns all required information for method
`rally.osclients.Clients.services`. If we use it, we will be able to remove
check for known service types and allow users to write plugins for services,
which is unknown for rally.

Also, after switching to `service.list`, we don't need
rally.consts.ServiceType any more.

Change-Id: Icfe235073eab6e1ca012eba6cabdcfb229b11f50
Closes-Bug: #1510490

commit_message:
Make gate-bindep-pypy voting

While OpenStack projects in general have PyPy unit tests non-voting,
bindep's unit tests run fine under it. Override the blanket
gate-.*-pypy pattern with a specific gate-bindep-pypy in voting
mode.

Add job to gate and fix wrong check label for bindep.

Change-Id: I5e7375ded7cd2714aede1ce913058d2e397f7f8f

commit_message:
[zmq] Driver optimizations for CALL

New DEALER-based publisher provided for CALL.
Futures-based reply waiting makes possible to
refuse using of REQ blocking socket and also
reduce number of openned sockets to a socket-per-target
instead of socket-per-message as it was for CALL.

Closes-Bug: #1517999

Optimized redis requests - request once instead of
per each message. This should be elaborated with an
autonomous nodes discovery mechanism to be correct
in general case.

Closes-Bug: #1517993

Reduced number of INFO log messages. Most of them switched
to the DEBUG level.

Closes-Bug: #1517997

Change-Id: Id017e79368cdc68613ddd7adef26411ea422dc8c

commit_message:
Display warning about weak password in fuelmenu

Display correct notice that password SHOULD but not must have valid
symbols because we just don't enforce strict password policy. And instead
fall into error we simply display a warning message when weak password
entered.

Change-Id: I3ba379aa6949ff6d9dc3ddd6f4a2d8111aebe1d2
Closes-Bug: #1480918

Refactor: Move FakeFlavorResource to compute_fakes.py.

Just like FakeServer and FakeResource, FakeFlavorResource should be in compute_fakes.py.

Implements: blueprint improve-flavor-unit-test

commit_message:
Refactor: Abstract columns out in TestFlavorList to avoid redundant code.

The columns has been set in each test case of TestFlavorList, which is not
necessary. This patch abstract it out and remove all redundant code.

Change-Id: Ideb2872f073755ac251bd603fd906410ea86c4ef
Implements: blueprint improve-flavor-unit-tes

Send notification and add event when a stack action is

I am skeptical of the word choice document. I suspect it applies more for prose than for code or even comments.

For example, I find that the URL for OpenStack's domain is always printed as http://www.openstack.org/ even though domain names are case-insensitive -- http://www.OpenStack.org/ works fine.

File paths are (almost) always case sensitive, but I see directories called "openstack" in a few places, and directories called "OpenStack" nowhere[1]. Even taking into account the word choice convention, we must continue to use the lowercase form in this case, to avoid breaking things.

[1] http://paste.openstack.org/show/479163/'}, {'account_id': 16986, 'date': '2015-11-18 10:05:15.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

commit_message:
OpenStack typo

According to the word choice convention in
http://docs.openstack.org/contributor-guide/writing-style/word-choice.html
We should use OpenStack instead of Openstack.

Closes-bug: #1516634

Change-Id: If4fd264635549c5b21c80e91b606142c5f9ae3a4

commit_message:
add manager.do_mkbootstrap func

do_mkbootstrap func, which adds possibility to build
 custom bootstrap image based on ubuntu-trusty.
Allows:
* install custom packages
* prepare matadata.yaml
* pack all bootstrap files into archive

Implements: blueprint dynamically-build-bootstrap
Related-Bug: #1444090
Change-Id: Icac658b867fe1c5f5af8da64fd741d7a5f7bb6f9

commit_message:
Adds test for mac_spoofing

Test that MAC spoofing is enforced by Neutron security-groups and allowed when
port-security flag is turned off.

Enhances several helper functions to support multiple NICs

Partially Implements: blueprint ml2-ovs-portsecurity

Change-Id: Idc7e733a19f926894050db012efbd7a10f08c011

@Sam, 

I added one test case (no.13) to confirm the following in RFC2616(14.16).

http://paste.openstack.org/show/198039/

A response to a request for a single range MUST NOT be sent using the multipart/byteranges media type. A response to a request for multiple ranges, whose result is a single range, MAY be sent as a multipart/byteranges media type with one part.

But I could not find Content-Length here so I didn't put it. Is this case match to the following?

When an HTTP message includes the content of a single range (for example, a response to a request for a single range, or to a request for a set of ranges that overlap without any holes), this content is transmitted with a Content-Range header, and a Content-Length header showing the number of bytes actually transferred.

diff: http://paste.openstack.org/show/198038/"}, {'account_id': 2622, 'date': '2015-04-03 20:04:12.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

RFC 7233 clarifies this nicely:

   A server MUST NOT generate a multipart response to a request for a
   single range, since a client that does not request multiple parts
   might not support multipart responses.  However, a server MAY
   generate a multipart/byteranges payload with only a single body part
   if multiple ranges were requested and only one range was found to be
   satisfiable or only one range remained after coalescing.  A client
   that cannot process a multipart/byteranges response MUST NOT generate
   a request that asks for multiple ranges.

Basically, if the client asked for multiple ranges but only one was satisfiable, then the server can choose: either a multipart/byteranges response with one part, or a single-part response.'}, {'account_id': 12193, 'date': '2015-04-06 01:42:55.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

@Sam, Thanks for the info about RFC 7233.

Our current implementation for a case that the client asks for multiple ranges but only one is satisfiable, swift behavives as a single-part response. According to RFC 2616 (see above comment), we might have a Content-Length header in the response. But it seems to be not exist.
So I was thinking about we need to add it in the future.

I added the case that we discussed here as test case no.13 and the code is in the url (diff). If possible, could you please merge it to this patch?'}, {'account_id': 2622, 'date': '2015-04-06 18:36:12.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 2622, 'date': '2015-04-06 18:59:01.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

I added an additional test case for 2 ranges requested, 1 satisfiable. However, I did not require that the response be a single-part response; I don't want to be stricter than HTTP requires me to be. Just like RFC 7233 says, I allowed for either a 206 single-part response, or a 206 multipart/byteranges with a single byte range."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-04-06 19:46:42.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified+1

LGTM!'}, {'account_id': 14967, 'date': '2015-05-25 18:27:31.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 14619, 'date': '2015-05-25 19:02:51.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 16233, 'date': '2015-05-26 13:25:07.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 2696, 'date': '2015-05-26 15:51:21.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

I think the choice offered by RFC 7233 is a false.  Swift cares about client backward compatibility, even for stupid clients.  So whatever choice between the two responses offered by RFC 7233 Swift chooses to implement, a stupid client can code to.  (By "stupid", I mean not able to accept either of the responses that are "valid" per the RFC.)  Then we can't change it without breaking the stupid client(s).  I think when faced with this kind of conflict in the past, we tend to not make the desired Swift change so as to not break the stupid client.

So I think Swift will need to "stick with" the response type it picked for multi-range requests where only one range could be satisfied.  So there's actually benefit in having the functional test expect that response: prevent future Swift devs from potentially breaking clients, even within the "valid" bounds specified by the RFCs.

I'm not particularly adamant about this, but I do think it's worth considering.  This may be a case of pretending you have more freedom because an RFC says something when in practice, you're bound by existing clients you don't want to break.'}, {'account_id': 16206, 'date': '2015-06-16 03:46:42.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 13104, 'date': '2015-07-15 23:18:17.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1

Add job for networking-ofagent

This change adds check job for networking-ofagent project and
avoids to run python3 job for stable/icehouse.

Change-Id: Idcd91e445cfaeffd42e440602031f906c6f2dbcc

commit_message:
[Ironic] Fix volumes metadata for ironic role

Ironic should use "min" allocation size for OS
And place /var/log to separate partition.

Closes-bug: #1511353

commit_message:
LBaaS V2 service not needed with Octavia driver

The q-lbaasv2 screen service deployed by DevStack is not needed
when the Octavia driver is used. Running the service will confuse
operators and simply generate error messages in the log. The
service will still be run for other drivers, such as HAProxy, that
require the service. In addition, the README was updated to explain
how to configure other drivers and to use the correct git tags for
Octavia.

Change-Id: Icad7da99641cb0e87e51bb90999dcb44ae738ffd
Closes-Bug: #1509475

commit_message:
Add fuel-tasklib to fuel library using tox

This project was deprecated out of stackforge and
needs a home in fuel-library, where it current is used
as a testing library.

Tox is used so it can call tasks-test-requirements.txt
with relative paths correctly. Otherwise, the relative
path would have to be guessed based on where a user
might call it.

Change-Id: I742e167a77cca2ae47436cce7b1baf63e70fe063
Closes-Bug: #1507208
(cherry picked from commit d2cdb1fa973517666d88bd63a7a37586d8e56990)

commit_message:
Fix options for pluto per-peer logging

--perpeerlogbase option has no effect without --perpeerlog. [1]
Moreover there is no need to create 'logs' dir as there is a 'log'
dir that can be reused.

Also fixed indentation issue for enable_detailed_logging option
declaration.

[1] http://linux.die.net/man/8/ipsec_pluto

DocImpact
Related-Bug: #1308730
Change-Id: Ie5ef72c2abd83b9b1114d90a6c7294cc34174018

commit_message:
[Rally] enable more services for gate-rally-dsvm-verify-full

This patch enables sahara,heat,neutron for "full" mode of
gate-rally-dsvm-verify job.
Also this patch adds ability to turn on ceilometer in future.

These services are needed to cover more options of config generator
for tempest in `rally verify` cmd.

Change-Id: I3d3eeac92bcf7559000db536ffde659a25081931

commit_message:
tripleo: add puppet-{aodh,gnocchi}

Aodh & Gnocchi are two OpenStack components part of Telemetry that we
want to integrate in TripleO.

This patch:
* makes sure we clone the modules during TripleO jobs.
* gate both modules with tripleo-nonha job like it's done for some other
  modules

Change-Id: I585a353d7a4b6b0cc8b58f91c1ffbd9b27f118c5

commit_message:
Add non-voting constraints jobs to glance

Adds all needed -constraints jobs to glance's check queue as non-voting

Depends-On: Ibbeabdf65c1405bf4d35e21375636dcc4583bbc2
Implements Blueprint: Requirements-Management

commit_message:
Disable TLS by default

Allow deploy without TLS by default and force user enable
and configure it if she needed to use secure connections
to public OpenStack endpoints.

Change-Id: I1a5603b172ac77389423c7de8c22ddaa69d87abb
Closes-Bug: #1495466

If DVR is enabled and an l3-agent is restarted, associating a floatingip

commit_message:
Fix dvr_local_router.floating_ip_added_dist failure after agent restart

If DVR is enabled and an l3-agent is restarted, associating a floatingip
to an existing vm on the compute node where the l3-agent was restarted
will fail.  This commit fixes the floating_ip_added_dist method in
dvr_local_router.py so that self.rtr_fip_subnet will be created if
it is 'None' prior to the attempt to call the get_name() method on
it.

Closes-Bug: #1515341
(cherry-picked from commit da3de52c507544c84463a037acac3b2b24a37fe0)

Conflicts:
	neutron/tests/unit/agent/l3/test_dvr_local_router.py

Change-Id: I43b326f8b313b5be2d2d1f28c8eb351e42624391

[{'created': '2015-11-27 07:48:27.000000000', 'message': 'Set default auth_plugin to token when creating SDK connection

This patch revises default auth_plugin type to token when creating
SDK connection. This is because Senlin service uses token and trust
to talk with other backend openstack services. For authenticate
method in sdk driver, auth_plugin type will be decided based on
credential given. If token is not provided, auth_plugin type will be
set to password.

Change-Id: Ief88395cf7f663a501e762028566d24ffde8dfcd
Closes-Bug: #1520440
'}]
commit_message:
Set default auth_plugin to token when creating SDK connection

This patch revises default auth_plugin type to token when creating
SDK connection. This is because Senlin service uses token and trust
to talk with other backend openstack services. For authenticate
method in sdk driver, auth_plugin type will be decided based on
credential given. If token is not provided, auth_plugin type will be
set to password.

Change-Id: Ief88395cf7f663a501e762028566d24ffde8dfcd
Closes-Bug: #1520440

commit_message:
Check missed IPSet utility using neutron-sanity-check

In some case, host may lack ipset utility (e.g., due to a
dependency issue)

This patch allows checking IPSet utility support from CLI:
    neutron-sanity-check --ipset_installed

Or using configuration options, for example:
    neutron-sanity-check --config-file /etc/neutron/neutron.conf
    --config-file /etc/neutron/plugins/ml2/ml2_conf.ini


Closes-Bug: #1510680
Change-Id: I2b9d6b13087a970bb0919a8217e428ce60d6e0c3
