commit_message:
Avoid conflicts with ceilometer.conf in dispatcher tests

This makes sure a critical configuration value
(filter_service_activity) used in the ceilometer dispatcher tests
is explicitly set in the setUp of the test. Otherwise a conflicting
value in /etc/ceilometer/ceilometer.conf can cause tests to fail.

Efforts to make a solution which just ignores
/etc/ceilometer/ceilometer.conf were confounded by too much "helpful"
magic in oslo_config. Given that this dispatcher will be leaving the
gnocchi repo soonish, a long trip down a rabbit hole was skipped.

Change-Id: I8f270183d6c38de0b4088166ddc2da687576a752
Closes-Bug: #1463889

commit_message:
Ensure the indexer is disconnected in gabbi fixtures

An index.connect() was added in commit 0620d841 but no corresponding
disconnect(). There's evidence that not properly disposing of the
associated engine facade may be causing test failures when
sufficient gabbi fixtures end up in the same process (this requires
a relatively low number of available cores).

Even if the lack of disconnect is not the cause of that, it is still
a correct thing to have.

Change-Id: I53d6ffbdead5ee959521131aecb2d7b58b6f8dd6

tests: start/stop coord before using it

Luckily the driver we use never needed that, but it may not work for all
tooz drivers.

Change-Id: I7310dfa5038ef8851a5b2730b2940915c8cfaaa2

commit_message:
Add the missing arg of RetryRequest exception in _lock_subnetpool

RetryRequest exception defined in oslo.db need be called with a arg
which describes the inner exception. _lock_subnetpool method missed this
arg, and this patch adds it.

Change-Id: I44869c97ecd7d59d40d8793c71515067a237150b
Closes-Bug: #1506818

commit_message:
Handle a 404 when posting a new named metric

If the resource is not a uuid a 404 will happen from
GenericResourceController. However if the resource is a uuid but
does not exist, then None can be passed to the RBAC enforce, causing
an untrapped error. Instead if we have no resource, 404.

Change-Id: Ic7b4e46fdc9444a0df9c8e978d877b7c83a67eaf

commit_message:
Remove oslo.config boundary + Use new location of subunit2html

There's no reason to have upper boundary and it breaks the gate to force
old buggy versions.

And backport fe581719306bbb4de72b5ade0366ede7f594700c to stable/1.0:
The previous location is going away, this location is preferred.

Closes-Bug: #1489404
Change-Id: I0c8bbc760c8bae37e28572efe01ce22c73aa089e

commit_message:
Ensure that identity token in header is not an unicode string

We need all the headers to be safe strings so they can be joined
together and not become an unicode string in doing so.

This fixes a bug when creating an image with non-ascii characters in the
name.

This is required for python 2.6 compatibility.

Change-Id: I66ebc27edf4ccd8f903399da58705711c372536d
Closes-Bug: 1448080

Purpose of this fix is to have a clean log file with no deprecation warnings. In an environment where no quota_items is specified (leaving only defaults) in neutron.conf file, then no deprecation warnings should be present in the logs. But current code prints one even if there are no additional resources are registered to quota engine using quota_items. 
This fix moves printing of deprecation warning conditionally.'}, {'account_id': 10608, 'date': '2015-10-13 13:49:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

recheck'}, {'account_id': 642, 'date': '2015-10-13 14:47:02.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

Seems like a bit of a bike shed fix, but if you're not specifying quota items now I'm having a hard time coming up with reasons you'd suddenly want them later, or more specifically, how seeing a deprecation message the entire time would help or hurt that."}, {'account_id': 10608, 'date': '2015-10-13 15:03:33.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

deprecation warnings are to tell you "you're doing something you should stop doing because that is going to go away". As such, they should *only* be printed if/when you are doing that thing you should stop doing. Not all the time for everyone. This change appears to fix that. LGTM.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-10-13 19:21:18.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Verified+1

commit_message:
Remove duplicate deprecation messages for quota_items option

The option is already marked for deprecation using oslo.config
mechanism, so there is no need to output more warnings here.

Change-Id: I5db439a0b87c49a52f3f5c063d0fd90819f3e932
Closes-Bug: #1504312

commit_message:
Make nova server_interface function calls work

This patch add a new input parameter 'server_id' for all nova
server_interface related function calls to make them work.
It also removes update_server_interface and
find_server_interface methods since they are not supported by
Nova API.

Change-Id: I68f09c1f8f247b4db55eff87f771ec7a27f1be9b

[{'created': '2015-11-18 01:38:19.000000000', 'message': "DVR, add_router_interface: check for no subnets

The bug report specifies the following sequence of actions to reproduce
the issue:

1) Create DVR router

2) Set it as a gateway on an external network with
no subnet.

3) Add a router interface on an internal subnet. This will return error
500.

In practice, what matters is that the l3 scheduler gets triggered(in
this case, by adding the interface). At some point, it will call
'get_subnet_ids_on_router' to figure out what the subnet id is. Since we
have added no subnets, that is an empty list and results in an index out
 of range and a 500 error.

Added a check to verify if we do have a list of fixed_ips before trying
to get the first element.

Change-Id: If32db500aa3a0c299a5f19c33c05237e8e407e08
Closes-Bug: 1452458
"}, {'created': '2015-11-18 01:52:08.000000000', 'message': "DVR, add_router_interface: check for no subnets

The bug report specifies the following sequence of actions to reproduce
the issue:

1) Create DVR router

2) Set it as a gateway on an external network with
no subnet.

3) Add a router interface on an internal subnet. This will return error
500.

In practice, what matters is that the l3 scheduler gets triggered(in
this case, by adding the interface). At some point, it will call
'get_subnet_ids_on_router' to figure out what the subnet id is. Since we
have added no subnets, that is an empty list and results in an index out
 of range and a 500 error.

Added a check to verify if we do have a list of fixed_ips before trying
to get the first element.

Change-Id: If32db500aa3a0c299a5f19c33c05237e8e407e08
Closes-Bug: 1452458
"}, {'created': '2015-11-19 00:16:00.000000000', 'message': "DVR, add_router_interface: check for no subnets

When the l3 dvr scheduler gets triggered, perhaps by adding an interface
to a router, at some point the 'get_subnet_ids_on_router' will be
called, to figure out what the subnet id is for the given router.

It retrieves a list of ports for the device, then a list of ips (which
is an array with subnet_id/ip pairs). It then tries to take the first
item of the array, without checking if there are any elements first.
Therefore, if there aren't any subnets, it will crash.

Added a check to verify if we do have any elements in the list of
fixed_ips, before trying to retrieve the first element of the list. In
case there aren't any subnets, the port is skipped.

Change-Id: If32db500aa3a0c299a5f19c33c05237e8e407e08
Closes-Bug: 1452458
"}, {'created': '2015-11-20 20:08:08.000000000', 'message': 'Fix get_subnet_ids_on_router in dvr scheduler

Added a check to verify if we do have any elements in the list of
fixed_ips, before trying to retrieve the first element of the list, to
get the subnet id. There were no checks in the original code, so it
would crash.

Change-Id: If32db500aa3a0c299a5f19c33c05237e8e407e08
Closes-Bug: 1452458
'}]
commit_message:
Fix get_subnet_ids_on_router in dvr scheduler

Added a check to verify if we do have any elements in the list of
fixed_ips, before trying to retrieve the first element of the list, to
get the subnet id. There were no checks in the original code, so it
would crash.

Change-Id: If32db500aa3a0c299a5f19c33c05237e8e407e08
Closes-Bug: 1452458

commit_message:
Avoid race condition for reserved DHCP ports

This patch introduces mechanism similar to compare-and-swap
for updating reserved DHCP port.

This addresses a case when two DHCP agents that start nearly at
the same time are assigned to one network and there is a reserved
DHCP port in the network. Then each of agents will try to use it
because agents don't check if reserved port is still available.
Reserved DHCP port can be acquired by different agent between calls to
get_active_networks and update_port, so this patch adds a check for
this case.

Change-Id: I0277ab537ff9d3a664c03ea291b9ec2b0e784dbb
Closes-Bug: #1425402

commit_message:
Lower l2pop "isn't bound to any segement" log to debug

Per the discussion in bug 1362242, the log statement doesn't
appear to be associated with anything bad happening. Therefore,
this patch lowers the log level from WARNING to DEBUG to avoid
polluting operator's logs.

Change-Id: I55b6d1d30ed2ed55659c9a6809531cfcbc57f17c
Signed-off-by: Ryan Moats <rmoats@us.ibm.com>
Closes-Bug: 1362242

I noticed this when debugging some grenade issues failures.

An include of grenade/functions stores the current value of XTRACE
(on) and disables xtrace for the rest of the import.

We then include devstack's "functions" library, which now overwrites

it just happens to be turned on.

so when we finish sourcing a file, we always restore the tracing value
to what it was when we entered.

Some files had already discovered this.  In general there is
inconsistency around the setting of the variable, and a lot of obvious
copy-paste.  This brings consistency across all files by using
_XTRACE_* prefixes for the sotre/restore of tracing values.

commit_message:
Namespace XTRACE commands

I noticed this when debugging some grenade issues failures.

An include of grenade/functions stores the current value of XTRACE
(on) and disables xtrace for the rest of the import.

We then include devstack's "functions" library, which now overwrites
the stored value of XTRACE the current state; i.e. disabled.

When it finishes it restores the prior state (disabled), and then
grenade restores the same value of XTRACE (disabled).

The result is that xtrace is incorrectly disabled until the next time
it just happens to be turned on.

The solution is to name-space the store of the current-value of xtrace
so when we finish sourcing a file, we always restore the tracing value
to what it was when we entered.

Some files had already discovered this.  In general there is
inconsistency around the setting of the variable, and a lot of obvious
copy-paste.  This brings consistency across all files by using
_XTRACE_* prefixes for the sotre/restore of tracing values.

Change-Id: Iba7739eada5711d9c269cb4127fa712e9f961695

commit_message:
Remove ssh args to ensure pipelining is working

The ssh args that we have been carrying are overriding
base functionality in Ansible which can cause intermitent
issues. To correct this issue I removed our ssh-args which
will use the default ssh arguments provided by ansible core.

Change-Id: If61d875a58e466ec07cb6818040e83f1612b4f18
Related-Bug: https://github.com/ansible/ansible/pull/9246
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>
(cherry picked from commit c7ce0982ff0c5e357fe957c9f929a9bf71deed7c)

commit_message:
Define gitshasrc in case of custom build flow

If we are running custom build flow, we are not using
fetch_upstream flow, that's why variable gitshasrc should be
redefined

Change-Id: Iebe4c18c8701d7c89bca2fa1abeb8b4840e69cf5

commit_message:
Make image_client use **kwargs

As we discussed on
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-July/068864.html
All http POST/PUT methods need to contain **kwargs as their arguments.
This patch makes image_client use **kwargs.
This patch doesn't cover create/update_image because these methods
are used at many places and it is nice to separate them from this
patch for easy implementation/review.

Partially implements blueprint consistent-service-method-names

Change-Id: I1976623d512cf3f622d81805d68cc994d359cf74

commit_message:
Add output API calls implementations

Add output APIs support for output-show and output-list
commands. Now output-show and output-list uses output
calls instead of requesting stack get.

implements bp api-call-output
Change-Id: I1bc1cee1c78ecf0c9a18ecc0a871d38e4141e0f7
Depends on: Ia24b24f59e2c592801e4e670ba5510f642ecf45c

commit_message:
Tuple constants in revocation engine

Turn list constants in the revocation engine to tuples to increase
engine performance.

commit_message:
Remove "s" from imange clients' method

The object is a single, but some methods of image namespace client
contain "s" which means multiple objects.
For the consistency of service clients, we need to remove the "s"
from these methods.

Partially implements blueprint consistent-service-method-names

Change-Id: Id21767e38d74e1275eea64f91143f06874a7b323

commit_message:
Add _show_resource to EncryptedVolumeType

Currently cinder doesn't support to_dict
method for it's resources, so we should add
override _show_resource method for
Cinder::EncryptedVolumeType.

Change-Id: Id9cd115f7029864b9af241eb00c086e9b9f5dd22
Closes-bug: #1520473

[{'created': '2015-11-27 08:36:01.000000000', 'message': 'Fis mistypes with affect on API

1. screnarios -> scenarios
2. removed unused code (
      assign element of dictionary before return of this element only,
      redundant parenthesis - again,

commit_message:
Fis mistypes with affect on API

1. screnarios -> scenarios
2. spended_time -> spent time (used only at 1 place)
3. rename few test methods (not groups)
4. removed unused code (
      assign element of dictionary before return of this element only,
      redundant parenthesis - again,
      comeback of mutable defaults - again,
      variable, which redefined on the next line in if-else)

Change-Id: I68ffdc85c2d1289d7ab6ef6a7f4084c19e7afcf9
Related-Bug: #1513777

Remove iso8601 dependency

Murano does not import and use this module directly,
no need to list it in the requirements.

commit_message:
Add Fedora 23 as supported distribution

Fedora 23 was released on 03-NOV-2015[1]
Related note: Fedora 21 will reach its End Of Life (EOL) on 01-DEC-2015,
a corresponding patch to remove support for it can be removed at that
time.

[1] http://permalink.gmane.org/gmane.linux.redhat.fedora.core.announce/3017

Change-Id: If2ff0114f2cfb3a1eca111932d916dc9947d0098

commit_message:
Add Cinder Block Device role

This commit adds a new Cinder-Block-Device node role.

This role requires only entire disk space, hence should not be any
other partitions on chosen disk. Also disks for a new role should
not be mounted by partition manager.

blueprint cinder-block-device-driver

Change-Id: I0279adffc3866608109efd23845ef2aa365e0704

commit_message:
Add possibility to serialize disks information

This commit adds a new feature - serialization of disks.

Currently Nailgun doesn't have possibility to serialize disk
information, like which disks used by some role or which volume
groups will be created.

This information will be serialized to yaml format and then will be
passed to Astute.

Related blueprint cinder-block-device-driver

Change-Id: I3eff5521beb3588c1de1802e562cecfe25a32d76

commit_message:
Convergence: Re-trigger failed resource for latest traversal

Presently, when a resource of previous traversal completes its action
successfully we re-trigger this resource for latest traversal.(since
the latest traversal will be waiting for its completion)

However, if a resource of previous traversal fails we do not
re-trigger which leads to latest traversal waiting endlessly.

This patch re-triggers the resource for latest traversal even when
the resource fails.

Change-Id: I9f70878ad7f1ff7c2facb950e496681425b54fc4

Here is a an easy fix which will handle most of the failures

def exception_to_validation_msg(e):
    return getattr(e,'error',{}).get('error',{}).get('message',None)

commit_message:
Displays error message for template validation

This fix helps to propagate the error message received from the http
client.  The error message was hidden by a generic message instead of
using the information provided by the backend service.

Closes-Bug: #1262328
Change-Id: I6aedbafceabf036e4b21a0ae91c03f37b55a2f73

commit_message:
Fix VolumeType projects property handling

Currently using projects property in Cinder::VolumeType
occurres many errors. This patch fixes incorrect using
KeystoneClientPlugin method and handling of volume_type_access
list response.

Change-Id: Ib66766b33736911761cc0038be9764040fcf6f1f
Closes-bug: #1520270

[{'created': '2015-11-25 11:26:24.000000000', 'message': "Bump some timeouts on post-puppet cluster restart

On slow machines the resource stop/start operations after Puppet run can
take a lot of time, we've seen a timeout on httpd start. This commit
introduces new, safer values.

The values aren't computed by some exact formula but estimated by
inspecting the slow failed environment and looking how much things took
to stop/start.

Change-Id: I9556085424fa3008d7f596578b58e7c33a336f75
"}]
commit_message:
Bump some timeouts on post-puppet cluster restart

On slow machines the resource stop/start operations after Puppet run can
take a lot of time, we've seen a timeout on httpd start. This commit
introduces new, safer values.

The values aren't computed by some exact formula but estimated by
inspecting the slow failed environment and looking how much things took
to stop/start.

Change-Id: I9556085424fa3008d7f596578b58e7c33a336f75

[{'created': '2015-11-24 18:34:42.000000000', 'message': 'Extends system tests to use devops template

Runtime changing of yaml config via environment variable use !os_env

Yaml configuration compiled only when test started, than increase
    creation speed of test plan and improve isolation of config files

Using name of yaml file for link config and test case instead of the

commit_message:
Extends system tests to use devops template

Runtime changing of yaml config via environment variable use !os_env

Add validator for unique file name of yaml config file. We should have
    unique file names in system_test/tests_templates/tests_configs

Yaml configuration compiled only when test started, than increase
    creation speed of test plan and improve isolation of config files

Using name of yaml file for link config and test case instead of the
    test-group node in yaml file before

Add several types of group names:
    case_group.CONFIG
    case_gorup(CONFIG)
    case_gorup[CONFIG]
    case_gorup{CONFIG}

Add default devops template
    system_test/tests_templates/devops_configs/default.yaml

Use devops config in ceph_all_on_neutron_vlan.yaml

Implements blueprint template-based-testcases
Change-Id: Ib5ae4126041b2aad059199e93d0c78457125b1fe

commit_message:
re-implement thread safe fnmatch

fnmatch is not thread safe for versions <= 2.7.9. We have used
it in some places without any lock for concurrency scenario. This patch
re-implements a thread safe match() which is very similar to fnmatch by
using its translate function.

Co-Authored-By: ZhiQiang Fan <aji.zqfan@gmail.com>
Change-Id: I4b6c2ea72841201519144eb09ecf8c82b16b6143
ref: https://hg.python.org/cpython/rev/fe12c34c39eb
Closes-Bug: #1519767

Fix location for loadbalancer_pool_scheduler_driver

Neutron advanced services had splited from Neutron repo in Kilo,
this patch use LBaaS location for loadbalancer_pool_scheduler_driver
in neutron.conf.

commit_message:
Add option for detailed template error

NOTE: The title of original patch is incorrect, because
patch adds additional yaml parsing with detailed error,
but there's no adding new option for this.

If there is some error during parsing template or
env file, CSafeLoader errors doesn't contains snippet
from template. So, we need to use SafeLoader for more
informative error with snippet from parsed template.

Change-Id: Ied0a573a00eb5f564dea0c636da1301de5de9ea7
Closes-bug: #1496361
(cherry picked from commit 54a1715e348720ab31b5d2e38035bf429471cdbe)

Add basic Quobyte Cinder driver documentation

Gives some short hints on basic concepts of the Quobyte Cinder driver
and where to get help.

Implements: blueprint quobyte-cinder-driver-doc

commit_message:
Fix ScaleIO driver provisioning key

In the ScaleIO Cinder volume driver, the parameter 'sio:provisioning'
is wrong. It should be 'sio:provisioning_type' instead. As a result of
this error, the volume is always provisioned as 'thick' even if user
wants to provision a 'thin' volume.

This patch corrects this parameter.

Closes-Bug: #1519611
Change-Id: I7c3b0256af3c30c2f375c0f9373646d3f58cd0d0

commit_message:
Make cluster-policy-detach return 400 instead of 404

When the referenced policy is not found (with cluster found already) or
the policy is not attached to the cluster (i.e. binding not found), the
request is a bad request (400). We should not return 404 (not found)
in this case.

Change-Id: Id1c0a0fb53c214c22b488df7febddcfe95bc120d
Partial-Bug: #1518209

commit_message:
Let cluster-policy-attach return 400 rather than 404

When the specified policy is not found (instead of the cluster not
found), we should return 400 (bad request) rather than 404 (not found).

Change-Id: I8ddf53e87b099b4d477da5af5a086f28ff8e0dbe
Partial-Bug: #1518209

commit_message:
Don't snapshot if server hasn't been created yet

If a server has not been created yet, do not to snapshot
when deleting if the deletion_policy is Snapshot, otherwise
an error raises: Instance None could not be found.

This patch fix another problem: get the status of server
resource by getting state[1] instead of state[0].

Change-Id: I44559df2f56d4f99e82208d776ab0609b6589e7c
Closes-Bug: #1517692

commit_message:
Improve message of the teardown.sh

Currently the teardown doesn't care about destroy other lxc
containers and destroys everything.
Same for logical volumes in the lxc volume group.

This tweaks the message to make it more clear.

Closes-Bug: #1518492

Change-Id: If8bbd9c8b6cea4d18ad982ee676e0480a88a1a4e

commit_message:
Implement tunable Ceilometer workers

This patch introduces an override for the number of Ceilometer workers:
 - ceilometer_api_workers
 - ceilometer_collector_workers
 - ceilometer_notification_workers

The values may be set in /etc/openstack_deploy/user_variables.yml
and if they are unset, half the number of available vCPU's will be
used instead.

Backport Note:
The var locations were changed in the following patch and apply to
Liberty+ only:
 - https://review.openstack.org/209333

Implements: blueprint gate-split
Change-Id: I126d735b737237cde27dde8a864e945d037e2e4a

commit_message:
Add assert:supports-upgrade tag to Neutron

Based on requirements defined in [1], I believe that is
a fair statement to claim cold upgrades support for Neutron.

Rolling upgrades are not too far off, but not within our reach
to allow us to claim assert:support-rolling-upgrade, just yet.
This is mainly because of lack of full stack integration testing
with services arranged in a mid-upgrade manner. This is planned
for Mitaka, and I count to reconsider adding the latter tag in
time for the release.

[1] http://governance.openstack.org/reference/tags/assert_supports-upgrade.html#requirements

Change-Id: I691325fe5f8562fb59239ecde75f0992a53d599e

migrations and API upgrades.

commit_message:
Add xstatic projects to Horizon

Horizon packages many of its dependencies with xstatic hosted on pypi,
and they (mostly) have respective openstack projects for community
review. These should be listed as valid openstack projects within
governance.

Change-Id: Ie03bc7bd5c4f6f9c9133e45ad3b1d37f83cb224b

commit_message:
Add new image for tempest

Note, this image is slightly different to most others in Kolla in that
it's not a service designed to be deployed via Ansible. It's more a
'tool' type image that is spun up when needed.

Partially-Implements: blueprint tempest-gate

Change-Id: I1877c03d0804e57d274044aecb1055f847025bec

commit_message:
Code refactoring - Watcher Decision Engine package

This patchset is there to change the code structure.
The objective is to flatten the project file tree by merging
'api/' and 'framework/' into a single package. This also contains
some tidy ups in package naming (like using only singular nouns).

This should only affect file/folder names and their subsequent
import paths wherever they were used.

Change-Id: Ie903ba20ca5cf03b0b42efa60131d1b919b0c2c9

'}, {'created': '2015-08-30 08:10:52.000000000', 'message': "Convergence: Concurrency subtle issues

To avoid certain concurrency related issues, the DB update API needs to
be given the traversal ID of the stack intended to be updated. By making
this change, we can void having following at all the places:

    if current_traversal != stack.current_traversal:
        return

The check for current traversal should be implicit, as a part of stack's
store and state_set methods, where self.current_traversal should be used
as expected traversal to be updated. All the state changes or updates in
DB to the stack object go through this implicit check (using
update...where).

When stack updates are triggered, the current traversal should be backed
up as previous traversal, a new traversal should be generated and the
stack should be stored in DB with expected traversal as the previous
traversal. This will ensure that no two updates can simultaneously
succeed on same stack with same traversal ID. This was one of our
primary goal.

Following example cases describe the issues we encounter:

1. When 2 updates, U1 and U2 try to update a stack concurrently:

    1. Current traversal(CT) is X
    2. U1 loads stack with CT=X
    3. U2 loads stack with CT=X
    4. U2 stores the stack and updates CT=Y
    5. U1 stores the stack and updates the CT=Z

    Both the updates have succeeded, and both would be running until
    one of the workers does stack.current_traversal == current_traversal
    and bail out.

    Ideally, U1 should have failed: only one should be allowed in case
    of concurrent update. When both U1 and U2 pass X as the expected
    traversal ID of the stack, then this problem is solved.

2. A resource R is being provisioned for stack with current traversal
   CT=X:

    1. An new update U is issued, it loads the stack with CT=X.
    2. Resource R fails and loads the stack with CT=X to mark it as FAILED.
    3. Update U updates the stack with CT=Y and goes ahead with sync_point
       etc., marks stack as UPDATE_IN_PROGRESS
    4. Resource marks the stack as UPDATE_FAILED, which to user means that
       update U has failed, but it actually is going on.

    With this patch, when Resource R fails, it will supply CT=X as
    expected traversal to be updated and will eventually fail because
    update U with CT=Y has taken over.

Change-Id: I6ca11bed1f353786bb05fec62c89708d98159050

"}, {'created': '2015-11-16 12:20:05.000000000', 'message': "Convergence: Concurrency subtle issues

To avoid certain concurrency related issues, the DB update API needs to
be given the traversal ID of the stack intended to be updated. By making
this change, we can void having following at all the places:

    if current_traversal != stack.current_traversal:
        return

The check for current traversal should be implicit, as a part of stack's
store and state_set methods, where self.current_traversal should be used
as expected traversal to be updated. All the state changes or updates in
DB to the stack object go through this implicit check (using
update...where).

When stack updates are triggered, the current traversal should be backed
up as previous traversal, a new traversal should be generated and the
stack should be stored in DB with expected traversal as the previous
traversal. This will ensure that no two updates can simultaneously
succeed on same stack with same traversal ID. This was one of our
primary goal.

Following example cases describe the issues we encounter:

1. When 2 updates, U1 and U2 try to update a stack concurrently:

    1. Current traversal(CT) is X
    2. U1 loads stack with CT=X
    3. U2 loads stack with CT=X
    4. U2 stores the stack and updates CT=Y
    5. U1 stores the stack and updates the CT=Z

    Both the updates have succeeded, and both would be running until
    one of the workers does stack.current_traversal == current_traversal
    and bail out.

    Ideally, U1 should have failed: only one should be allowed in case
    of concurrent update. When both U1 and U2 pass X as the expected
    traversal ID of the stack, then this problem is solved.

2. A resource R is being provisioned for stack with current traversal
   CT=X:

    1. An new update U is issued, it loads the stack with CT=X.
    2. Resource R fails and loads the stack with CT=X to mark it as FAILED.
    3. Update U updates the stack with CT=Y and goes ahead with sync_point
       etc., marks stack as UPDATE_IN_PROGRESS
    4. Resource marks the stack as UPDATE_FAILED, which to user means that
       update U has failed, but it actually is going on.

    With this patch, when Resource R fails, it will supply CT=X as
    expected traversal to be updated and will eventually fail because
    update U with CT=Y has taken over.

Partial-Bug: #1512343
Change-Id: I6ca11bed1f353786bb05fec62c89708d98159050

commit_message:
Convergence: Concurrency subtle issues

To avoid certain concurrency related issues, the DB update API needs to
be given the traversal ID of the stack intended to be updated. By making
this change, we can void having following at all the places:

    if current_traversal != stack.current_traversal:
        return

The check for current traversal should be implicit, as a part of stack's
store and state_set methods, where self.current_traversal should be used
as expected traversal to be updated. All the state changes or updates in
DB to the stack object go through this implicit check (using
update...where).

When stack updates are triggered, the current traversal should be backed
up as previous traversal, a new traversal should be generated and the
stack should be stored in DB with expected traversal as the previous
traversal. This will ensure that no two updates can simultaneously
succeed on same stack with same traversal ID. This was one of our
primary goal.

Following example cases describe the issues we encounter:

1. When 2 updates, U1 and U2 try to update a stack concurrently:

    1. Current traversal(CT) is X
    2. U1 loads stack with CT=X
    3. U2 loads stack with CT=X
    4. U2 stores the stack and updates CT=Y
    5. U1 stores the stack and updates the CT=Z

    Both the updates have succeeded, and both would be running until
    one of the workers does stack.current_traversal == current_traversal
    and bail out.

    Ideally, U1 should have failed: only one should be allowed in case
    of concurrent update. When both U1 and U2 pass X as the expected
    traversal ID of the stack, then this problem is solved.

2. A resource R is being provisioned for stack with current traversal
   CT=X:

    1. An new update U is issued, it loads the stack with CT=X.
    2. Resource R fails and loads the stack with CT=X to mark it as FAILED.
    3. Update U updates the stack with CT=Y and goes ahead with sync_point
       etc., marks stack as UPDATE_IN_PROGRESS
    4. Resource marks the stack as UPDATE_FAILED, which to user means that
       update U has failed, but it actually is going on.

    With this patch, when Resource R fails, it will supply CT=X as
    expected traversal to be updated and will eventually fail because
    update U with CT=Y has taken over.

Partial-Bug: #1512343
Change-Id: I6ca11bed1f353786bb05fec62c89708d98159050

commit_message:
Change default endpoint for Keystone v3 to public

All of the other Openstack services have a 'public' default endpoint
type. Keystone has 'admin' default endpoint type. Why not make
Keystone compliant and change the default for Keystone v3 from 'admin'
to 'public'. Keystone v2 will remain the same with an 'admin' default.

Closes-Bug: #1457702
Change-Id: I515438477dba72c2a0c4595603000690511b5700

commit_message:
Create SDK connection with identity version set to v3

This patch sets identity service version to v3 when creating SDK
connection. This is necessary for the access to some keystone
resources that only supported in v3 API, like trust.

Change-Id: If07551bf948f073f58d4798aabbffe982fe37163
Closes-Bug: #1520453

commit_message:
Enable a new role for migrated node

When adding a node to a cluster, we should support an optional role to
be assigned to the node in the cluster. This patch adds support at DB
layer that the role can be renewed when migrating a node.

Change-Id: Ifd9a2b9b7e9e7e3377e8b69240d765b25c605228
Partial-Bug: 1465657

commit_message:
Remove google analytics

This patch removes the inclusion of google-analytics, which has nothing
to do in a free software project like OpenStack. In no way, we should
be including such a spy tool on all of our documentations. It is by the
way considered as a privacy breach and a very bad practice by
distributions like Debian, so at least there, the OpenStack theme has
to be patched anyway.

Change-Id: I4867292dcfb1a4d13822076208b349130e5c93b0

commit_message:
Functional: Use Magnum client to test container actions on Swarm bay

Leverage Magnum client to create a container on the bay we created,
and try to start and stop it then delete it.

Partially implements: blueprint swarm-functional-testing
Change-Id: I1dcd7e45442d674c565710a4e51ef58d8d0bb055

commit_message:
Refactoring HP 3PAR Manila Driver to be HPE

The HP 3PAR Manila driver was recently refactored to be HPE.

The same refactoring is being done to the documentation with
this patch. It is being done because the company managing the
HP 3PAR Manila driver is now Hewlett Packard Enterprise (HPE).

Closes-Bug: #1517283

Gateway device management API spec

Spec for managing the Gateway devices to support
HW VTEP and Router Peering use cases.

Implements blueprint gw-device-api

commit_message:
Add support for ilo drivers in lib/ironic

This commit adds support for configuring
proliant hardware with ilo driver(s)
(iscsi_ilo, agent_ilo and pxe_ilo) in Ironic
while starting devstack.

- gate-ironic-docs http://docs-draft.openstack.org/02/225602/1/check/gate-ironic-docs/dc63fd2//doc/build/html/ : SUCCESS in 6m 19s'}, {'account_id': 6773, 'date': '2015-09-21 10:51:21.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

I'm good with this move and I fully agree that the wiki seems to be easier to keep things up-to-date. But I would like to hear other peoples opinion on this matter, usually we require documentation for new drivers being proposed, should we start telling them to create a wiki page for their drivers instead? Or, should the driver documentation be part of the release ?"}, {'account_id': 6618, 'date': '2015-09-21 13:45:33.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2

(1 comment)

@Lucas, I'm totally fine with vendors maintaining/keeping wiki pages with info related to their drivers. 

When we started this drivers section in our documentation, does anyone remember/know what info we wanted to document? When I review, I just basically read/check that it makes sense."}, {'account_id': 9315, 'date': '2015-09-21 18:02:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Workflow-1

Just to see if we can do this in a better way still keeping it in ironic source tree.'}, {'account_id': 10343, 'date': '2015-09-21 19:35:46.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

I know Ramesh is investigating other options, but I wanted to vote here anyway. :)

Totally opposed to documentation on the wiki. Docs should be reviewed (anyone with an Launchpad account can edit the wiki without review).

Also, in-tree docs are so much prettier, and can be tied to a release if we decide to do so. :)

If there's too much overhead with keeping docs in tree, let's solve *that* problem rather than just removing the docs.

For some data: it doesn't seem like iLO doc updates are all that frequent: https://github.com/openstack/ironic/commits/master/doc/source/drivers/ilo.rst

And ditto for the iLO wiki: https://wiki.openstack.org/w/index.php?title=Ironic/Drivers/iLODrivers&action=history

So I'm not sure we need this."}, {'account_id': 6618, 'date': '2015-09-21 19:47:57.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: -Code-Review

Durn. I really hate reviewing docs. It doesn't make sense to have the wiki and docs intree, when one seems like a subset of the other. So whatever -- just make sure there is only one place that has the documentation."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-09-24 13:54:07.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Verified-1

This is not pursued now.'}]

commit_message:
Move iLO documentation to wiki

This commit removes the in-source documentation for
iLO driver and points it to wiki. Wiki is much more
easier to maintain with up-to-date information on
hardware specific information (firmware fixes,
workarounds, etc). Also, wiki captures the features
available in different releases in separate pages.

Change-Id: I7748e677f96861839c4c1609ab4024dff28770b2

commit_message:
Make OS_TEST_TIMEOUT configurable in tox.ini

This commit makes OS_TEST_TIMEOUT to be configurable
by an environment variable in tox.ini.  This is required
for running test_baremetal_server_ops on proliant hardware
which takes around 1500 seconds.

Change-Id: I4ad76882ebd9225141544dc484f33212b531bffd

commit_message:
Add --short option to "server list" command.

This option will shrink the command output to only UUID and server name.
It is an opposite option to --long, which could be useful.

Change-Id: I0ca18b87cb8363e553fa62945821f7bae8ea1868

commit_message:
[Rally] modify list of files for gate-rally-dsvm-verify-full

- Removed modules related unit tests: there are no reasons to launch full
  run when unit tests are changed.
- Adds rally/common/io/subunit_v2.py : this module is used to parse
  verification data

Change-Id: I1b33741311cf31b9430eeeaaae6629a0a9cd97da

commit_message:
Allow sharing of networks between nodegroups

Networks are considered as shared if they are in different nodegroups,
have the same Name, CIDR and Gateway values. No routes are geneated between
shared segments of networks.

Partial-Bug: #1484008
Partial-Bug: #1473047

Change-Id: Ifeaffd76d52a46d95918527c62c302ad356d2fe5
Blueprint: nodegroups-share-network-parameters

commit_message:
Remove hardcoded default docker client setting

This patch removes Hardcoded docker client settings and move them to configure
setting. Changes default value of DEFAULT_DOCKER_TIMEOUT from 10 to 60.

DEFAULT_DOCKER_TIMEOUT = 10 is too short, it brings troubles in some bad
networking environment (or bad performance swarm master), and this won't work
on gate.

The docker-py client's default value: DEFAULT_TIMEOUT_SECONDS = 60,
Suggest we set DEFAULT_DOCKER_TIMEOUT = 60,  as long as our rpc time_out.

There is a circle reference between magnum/common/docker_utils.py and
magnum/conductor/handlers/common/docker_client.py, so I merge them.

Co-Authored-By: Eli Qiao <liyong.qiao@intel.com>

Change-Id: I6046376cbf5eec6b0102956fd4e4f38b958dd80c
Closes-Bug: #1519714

commit_message:
WIP Remove Hardcoded Default docker client setting

This patch removes Hardcoded docker client settings and move them to configure
setting. Changes default value of DEFAULT_DOCKER_TIMEOUT from 10 to 60.

DEFAULT_DOCKER_TIMEOUT = 10 is too short, it brings troubles in some bad
networking environment (or bad performance swarm master), and this won't work
on gate.

The docker-py client's default value: DEFAULT_TIMEOUT_SECONDS = 60,
Suggest we set DEFAULT_DOCKER_TIMEOUT = 60,  as long as our rpc time_out.

Closes-Bug: #1519714
Change-Id: I8d8471ecb20076a64ba395207657dc048e139f97

commit_message:
Bump ironic-lib to 0.4.0

ironic-lib 0.4.0 has some changes needed for ironic so this bumps
it from 0.3.0 to 0.4.0. (To date, no ironic-related projects are
using ironic-lib yet.)

Change-Id: Id9b90761dbc580e57d3dc05ac67c8d1543dc621e

This reverts commit 9a4d719ea1a6ca63f527b5c78308fd288058d42b and creates a

commit_message:
Fix HTTP error codes due to invalid templates

This reverts commit 9a4d719ea1a6ca63f527b5c78308fd288058d42b and creates a
new exception type, InvalidGlobalResource, that is raised when a
non-existent template is referenced in the global environment and which
results in an HTTP 500 error.

This fixes the cases where we could return 404 or 500 errors as a result of
template validation failures, when we should return a 400 error.

Change-Id: I3c7b3182957448bb13514696cc2e12f5aaddd253
Closes-Bug: #1518458
Related-Bug: #1447194

commit_message:
Support creating signed url's in client

This change adds a function to create signed URLs, but does not create a
domain object or add them to the CLI.

Change-Id: I14d3c6aa6d7a5c8c5bf732e86cf9a24ca1342fad

commit_message:
Address hacking check H405.

Previously, there were a string of commits to keystone that addresed ignored
hacking checks. This commit does the same for H405 in keystonemiddleware. This
also modifies our tox.ini so that we no longer ignore H405 violations.

This is a non-functional change.

Change-Id: I7bbe99719feb39e96634c903991294c18c33112b
Closes-Bug: 1482773

system.

commit_message:
[config-ref] Add parallel_read_safe to ext.remote

To normally work on a multi processor machine.

If this flag is not set, the below error occurs with sphinx-build:

  Warning, treated as error:
  WARNING: the ext.remote extension does not declare if it is safe
  for parallel reading, assuming it isn't -
  please ask the extension author to check and make it explicit

Change-Id: I306c8b8db27a930e860c669b32d97c3a0fbbc32f

commit_message:
Consolidate two /sbin/ip commands into a single one

When determining the primary IP/IPv6 addresses on a system,
we can use the /sbin/ip command to filter them for us.  The
resulting address is parsed the same way for both address
families, so we can use just a single command.

Change-Id: I0471ff5a258a16a23061941ac38063dbf3d7c233

commit_message:
Rename TestShelveServer to TestServerShelve and sort the classes.

Three trivial fixes:
1. ShelveServer should be placed before ShowServer to keep the alpha beta order.
2. TestShelveServer should be TestServerShelve to keep the naming style.
3. TestServerShelve should be placed before TestServerStart to keep the alpha beta order.

Change-Id: Iea18389750a5518769ac16c864afb302c996f1b8

Fix 'action' call on cluster/node objects

The recent migration to keystoneauth1 in SDK has created problems more
than just a single problem. This patch fixes the 'action' calls.

commit_message:
Make '_short_id' method a public method

There are many exactly the same '_short_id' methods in v1/shell,
which are used as inner methods. This patch sets '_short_id' to be
a public method, it's also easy for test.

Change-Id: Id530ea01ca9815ef9a4aa95274fd303c25c698d3
Closes-bug: #1520014

commit_message:
Add gnocchiclient to requirements

Ceilometer moves its custom python-requests code to gnocchiclient library:

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/237538/

This change adds the new client lib to the global requirements.

Change-Id: I63f8735e2841291f5b66aeeab5fbdf957a001f0c

commit_message:
Update oslo.middleware to 3.0.0

This patch updates oslo middleware, to include the "program"
parameter in CORS middleware. This is required by glance, which
doesn't use the regular configuration file naming convention.

Change-Id: Icdbeba3d8622bd3470ead15128ee71f5c560add6

commit_message:
Fix IMAGE_URLS defaults for xenserver and ironic

Xenserver and Ironic were both unconditionally tacking on an additional image
to the `IMAGE_URLS` list. If the user specified that image themselves (as
directed by current documentation), then devstack would attempt to upload the
image to Glance twice, resulting in a 409 error, and devstack failing.

The fix is to only tack on that additional image if `IMAGE_URLS` has not been
supplied by the user.

Change-Id: I2eacf34f6361289abd82b824e82723034995ea84
Closes-Bug: 1451623

commit 0d42f01f68cbe4e480c51b63271bd3bdb41d8021,

in commit message. But netconfig.yaml.samle was added.

use HTTPS for tarball links

generated links.

When new repositories are added to a deliverable, we want to recognize
them as new and show all of the changes. The existing logic using the
generator expression fails with a StopIteration exception when there is
no repository matching the new version in the previous version.

Change-Id: Ifb426b89c85b21b18208a630fa5187a279e6ce2f
'}]
commit_message:
protect list-changes from new repos in a deliverable

When new repositories are added to a deliverable, we want to recognize
them as new and show all of the changes. The existing logic using the
generator expression fails with a StopIteration exception when there is
no repository matching the new version in the previous version.

Change-Id: Ifb426b89c85b21b18208a630fa5187a279e6ce2f

commit_message:
midonet: Make unit tests non-voting

gate-networking-midonet-python27 has been broken due to a few
Neutron changes.  Make it non-voting at least for the time being.
Do the same for py34 variant.
In order to make these changes, python-jobs and python3-jobs
are expanded.

Related-Bug: #1490917
Related-Bug: #1490921
Related-Bug: #1500740
Change-Id: I23f00de4adabea56db6ac22ddd3ee62dcee04e34

commit_message:
Fix glance.tests.unit.v1.test_registry_client

This patch fixes some common issues that prevented
glance.tests.unit.v1.test_registry_client from working with Python 3.

Change-Id: I27e8dbdd1075afe1be679a2d1573e4484591582d
Co-authored-by: Victor Stinner <vstinner@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Publicize the _convert_id call of Resource class

This renames the '_convert_ids' call to 'convert_ids' so that it becomes
a "public" method. It also adds some tests to this renamed method.

Change-Id: I904c86dd7a67f1f558bf8451c7f1fe438b906295
Closes-Bug: #1455190

commit_message:
Let node-join return 400 if cluster is not found

Part of a series of patches that will correct the returned status code
if some referenced objects cannot be found when performing some
operations on an entity.

commit_message:
Ignores endpoint_type if interface is provided

When a keystone session object is used, if endpoint_type and interface
is provided, we must use interface and drops endpoint_type.

Change-Id: I379e18f684aa5092f8adbeaebe98030053115767

commit_message:
Pushing events to users

This spec explains how we can provide a method for users to retrieve
events with a push mechanism instead of polling our API.

Change-Id: Ie04f9204f3ba0f75de32253f096f439c512cddee

I tried the current param validation status based on latest Magnum & Heat code. 
The status of validation on Bay-Creation is:

1. When create a Swarm Bay with invalid 'flavor_id':
The Bay creation will failed immediately with 'ERROR: Bad Request (HTTP 400)' and in there's an "InvalidParameter" exception in m-cond.log.

2. When create a K8S Bay with invalid 'flavor_id':
The Bay creation will not failed immediately, the Bay's status is "CREATE_IN_PROGRESS" and the Kube master instance is created. After pretty long time when Kube master instance config is done, the heat stack and K8S Bay's status change into "CREATE_FAILED", because the minion flavor id isn't existed, Kube Minion can not be created, and there're no check toward them.'}, {'account_id': 11536, 'date': '2015-11-24 16:48:07.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7: -Code-Review'}, {'account_id': 9591, 'date': '2015-11-24 21:15:48.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7:

@houming: for the failed k8s bay because of invalid flavor, if you run stack-show on the failed heat stack and check the stack_status_reason:

Resource CREATE failed: resources.kube_minions: 
resources[0]: Property error: resources.kube-minion.properties.flavor: Error validating value 'asdf.small': The Flavor ID (asdf.small) could not be found.

For Swarm, it's interesting that Heat responds somewhat differently, although the error message is similar.  Magnum conductor caught the exception from Heat with the message:

"InvalidParameterValue: ERROR: Property error: : resources.swarm_master.properties.flavor: : Error validating value 'asdf.small': The Flavor ID (asdf.small) could not be found."

From the discussion today, we agree that the focus should be to create a nice user experience in the case of error. Validation is a good part of that, but it seems that even with successful validation, the stack can fail because of other reasons.  Maybe we should decouple the two step and take a two-pronged approach: validation before calling heat, and getting heat stack_status_reason in case of failure.  In this case, the latter can be addressed in a separate patch.'}, {'account_id': 10515, 'date': '2015-11-25 05:07:50.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 8.'}, {'account_id': 10515, 'date': '2015-11-25 05:14:28.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 9.'}, {'account_id': 10515, 'date': '2015-11-25 05:15:59.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9:

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-11-17 21:32:54.000000000', 'message': "Validate baymodel's flavor when it's in req body

Currently the Baymodel's API parameter validation is
not enough to prevent further API failure, due to non-existed or
unprivileged OpenStack resources can be referenced and there're
no check/validation toward them.
We should check whether the flavor is existed when flavor_id is
in request body of Baymodel creation. If we didn't do this,
Baymodel with non-existed flavor_id is successfully created,
but the Bay creation use this Baymodel will fail.
This commit is the first one of serial API validation enhancements.

Change-Id: I34e97e32a952c5d65dd2c37fbd99c202456f4877
Patially-Implements: blueprint api-parameter-validation
"}, {'created': '2015-11-18 15:33:09.000000000', 'message': "Validate baymodel's flavor when it's in req body

Currently the Baymodel's API parameter validation is
not enough to prevent further API failure, due to non-existed or
unprivileged OpenStack resources can be referenced and there're
no check/validation toward them.
We should check whether the flavor is existed when flavor_id is
in request body of Baymodel creation. If we didn't do this,
Baymodel with non-existed flavor_id is successfully created,
but the Bay creation use this Baymodel will fail.
This commit is the first one of serial API validation enhancements.

Change-Id: I34e97e32a952c5d65dd2c37fbd99c202456f4877
Patially-Implements: blueprint api-parameter-validation
"}, {'created': '2015-11-22 15:15:04.000000000', 'message': "Validate baymodel's flavor when create a bay

Currently when we create a Bay, the API parameter validation toward
Bay's Baymodel is not enough to prevent bay creation failure,
due to non-existed or unprivileged OpenStack resources(flavor,
image, keypair, external_network, fixted_network) can be
referenced and there're no check/validation toward them.
We should check the existence of flavor in Baymodel creation.
A 404 NotFound will be raised if flavor in Baymodel isn't existed.

commit_message:
Validate baymodel's flavor when create a bay

Currently when we create a Bay, the API parameter validation toward
Bay's Baymodel is not enough to prevent bay creation failure,
due to non-existed or unprivileged OpenStack resources(flavor,
image, keypair, external_network, fixted_network) can be
referenced and there're no check/validation toward them.
We should check the existence of flavor in Bay creation.
A 404 NotFound will be raised if flavor in Bay's Baymodel isn't existed.

Change-Id: I34e97e32a952c5d65dd2c37fbd99c202456f4877
Patially-Implements: blueprint api-parameter-validation

commit_message:
Add log info for AMQP client

If librabbitmq is installed and can be imported correctly, it will
be used as AMQP client to connect RabbitMQ. Mark it in the log file.

Change-Id: I33807df67dd2fffa13c675324c8cc7ae716a210e
Signed-off-by: Kui Shi <skuicloud@gmail.com>

commit_message:
[Verify] Reworking unit tests for config.py [part 1]

1. The setUp() method was reworked
   because no one could understand how it worked.
2. Now ddt module is used where it is possible.
3. Some tests were refactored.

In some tests you will see that

    self.assertIn(sorted(expected)[0], sorted(result))

was replaced by

    for item in expected:
        self.assertIn(item, result)

because sorted(expected)[0] is only the first item from expected tuple.
So we always checked only one item from config section. The wrong behavior
was introduced by the following commit: I487806fe9a8ccd8528922cfaa2700df30961ef9b.
Now it is to be fixed.

Change-Id: Iaabc1a9fbd77e73bd9d28a30b29f9827a22e0bbd

commit_message:
Move netifaces to extras

netifaces is a very heavy requirement especially for
python clients, the code that uses netifaces is called
only in exception paths at least now. So let us move
this requirement to extras to reduce the time taken
to install oslo.utils.

Closes-Bug: #1517069
Change-Id: If3430364e49c1c0b1d9f4937bb67900380662728

deprecate timeutils.total_seconds()

We add method total_seconds to support Python 2.6, and now we dropped
Python 2.6, so just deprecate it.

Change-Id: Ie2b921c72fa96b9da057a0d4d3928222b188b2ab

commit_message:
Add functionality for creating Unix domain WSGI servers

This change modifies WSGI Server to allow creating Unix sockets
along with ip sockets. This would allow consuming projects to use
wsgi.Server to start Unix domain WSGI servers too, and thus get
rid of duplicating code.

Change-Id: I3de23efcd661b95cce6bbd1aa2c94abf0c814dbe

[{'created': '2015-11-22 16:50:47.000000000', 'message': 'Clarify usage docs

The policy docs were confusing because they start describing the
policy rule expressions but reference only one format. Rather than
provide a short and incorrect description in the intro, reference
the section that describes the format in full.

Also, the section that describes the rule format is moved right
after the intro since this is what the reader is going to be
looking for.

Also, the "Policy Rule Expressions" section is clarified. Since the
string representation is preferred, describe that first.

Change-Id: I69b74e2d0bd9cbe8fe447a1e0f8fa5ce2470b431
'}]
commit_message:
Clarify usage docs

The policy docs were confusing because they start describing the
policy rule expressions but reference only one format. Rather than
provide a short and incorrect description in the intro, reference
the section that describes the format in full.

Also, the section that describes the rule format is moved right
after the intro since this is what the reader is going to be
looking for.

Also, the "Policy Rule Expressions" section is clarified. Since the
string representation is preferred, describe that first.

Change-Id: I69b74e2d0bd9cbe8fe447a1e0f8fa5ce2470b431

commit_message:
Correct invalid doc references

Since the checks are defined in a private module, the docs for them
weren't being generated. The docs are moved to the public symbols so
that they'll be generated.

Also, there were several references from public docs to private
symbols. These are changed since any references to private symbols
aren't going to be able to link to the private symbol docs since
they're not generated.

Change-Id: I27c666479ecb978ad6bf21dc2ad80ef0265f62c5

commit_message:
[verify] Fix calculation number of tests

Only `status` method updates counters. Since _post_parse method can add
new tests, counters can be outdated.
This patch removes counters and moves calculation to `total` property.

Change-Id: Ia1bd3fb7ffd2ad15657619769609477498580e50

build metric list on init

we shouldn't need to recalculate metric list of resource every
single sample since it's a static file.

commit_message:
Fix create pool error

Zaqar client threw AttributeError while
executing pool create command.

This patch fixes the error.

Change-Id: I69b38ad1ffba257497b4f37709e0031ce2be99da
Closes-Bug: #1517268

commit_message:
Rewrite README file

* reorder sections
* add missing links on fasteners, oslo.concurrency and openstack-dev
* use ".. warning::" warning for the deprecation
* use reStructured Text syntax for the Documentation, Source and Bugs
  links
* use ``code markup`` for code
* Replace installation command "python setup.py install" with
  "pip install lockfile": pip is now prefered in 2015 and the command
  gives the PyPI name of the project (which is not obvious, I would
  expect "pylockfile", not "lockfile")
* fix other reStructured Text syntax errors

Change-Id: I386b9aa31b3c79589fe4d93f722aeccb3a8577ef

commit_message:
Change arp_send to arping

The fix to ns_IPaddr2 is added in order to make sure that we
are sending gratuitous ARP on failover. Also ocf_run is used
as it is necessary on CentOS platform for running ARPPING.

Closes-Bug: #1463382

Change-Id: I4104bc79a3ad0fabe9a7736a6b9c820aa0b09f37

commit_message:
gerritbot: update Puppet OpenStack branches

This patch aims to get IRC notications for the new stable/liberty and
stop stable/icehouse..

* drop stable/icehouse (not supported anymore)
* add stable/liberty (new branch)

Change-Id: I950d04177125761e676777f153789595e4bac80b

commit_message:
fix ceilometerclient functional gate job

The job always fails because it can't checkout Aodh
because openstack/aodh is missing from PROJECTS in the functional jobs.

This change fixes this.

Change-Id: I4d77d6ef0c1baa2c79a60661ef22a0320a96f938
